title:
rhubarb & tarragon destructured pie with white chocolate
espuma
directions: For the shortbread, mix all ingredients by hand to get a rather crumbly dough with big lumps. Spread these crumbs on a parchment lined baking sheet and bake for 15-20 minutes at 150°C (300°F).

Prepare the espuma by melting white chocolate in water-bath. Mix milk and sugar, pour it over the chocolate. Whisk to obtain a smooth mixture. Add the liquid cream. Mix and let cool for 3 hours. Pour into a siphon, add 2 gas cartridges. Put in a cool place until serving.

Assemble the dessert by starting with a generous layer of sauce in the bowls, top with the shortbread crumbs and finish with the white chocolate espuma. Assemble right before you are ready to serve, so the shortbread does not become soggy.

title: chili-glazed salmon with asian salad greens
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine 2 tablespoons Wish-Bone Light(R) Asian Sesame Ginger Vinaigrette Dressing, chili sauce and 1 green onion. Arrange salmon in 8-inch glass baking dish, then brush with dressing mixture. Bake 10 minutes or until salmon flakes with a fork.

Meanwhile, combine remaining Dressing with carrot juice in small bowl. Toss hot rice noodles with 1/4 cup Dressing mixture in medium bowl. Toss cabbages, snow peas and cilantro with remaining Dressing mixture in serving bowl. Top with noodles, then salmon. Sprinkle with remaining green onion.
tags: wish-bone light asian sesame ginger vinaigrette dressing

title: garlic chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Heat the oil in a Dutch oven and fry the garlic, celery, rosemary and thyme for 2 minutes. Place the chicken in the Dutch oven, cover and roast for 2 hours. Uncover and cook for a further 15 minutes. Serve with bread.

title: apple pancakes
directions: In a bowl, mix flour with milk. Mix in egg, peeled and grated apples, vanilla extract, and sugar.
Heat a small amount of oil in a small frying pan. Remove any excess oil with a paper towel.
With a soup ladle, pour batter into frying pan. When bubbles form, flip pancake and cook on the other side.
Make the pancakes one at a time.
Serve with powdered sugar and cinnamon, or just honey, if desired.

title: sauteed chicken with coriander, mushrooms and sausage
directions: Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a frying pan, add the sausage, garlic, and coriander, and saute.
When the mixture starts to brown, add the mushrooms, and fry for a few minutes.
Add the chicken, season with salt and a bit of lemon juice and cook for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: start your appetite artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in 8-inch baking dish. Bake uncovered 20 minutes or until heated through. Serve with wheat crackers or your favorite dippers.

title: sage roasted pork tenderloin with carbonara cabbage
directions: Place salt, pepper, garlic, sage and olive oil in a food processor; puree until sage and garlic are blended. Season pork generously with the rub. Grill over direct heat 20 minutes or until 145 degrees F. internal temperature, as measured with an instant-read thermometer. Allow to rest 5 minutes before slicing.
Meanwhile, in a large pot boil one gallon of water and salt. Add cabbage and blanch approximately 3 minutes or until tender: drain immediately and rinse in colander with very cold water.
In a small saucepan over low heat, simmer cream and garlic until reduced by half.

Place pancetta in a large skillet and brown until crisp. Remove and drain on paper towels. In same skillet, stir together cream, cabbage, pancetta, cheese and spinach over medium heat until warm. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with sliced pork.

title: mixed nuts brownies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
In a microwaveable bowl, add the cocoa and butter for 30 seconds, then stir and microwave for 30 more seconds. Stir and let it cool.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix well. Add the eggs one by one, then add the flour, mixed nuts, and chocolate. Mix but do not over-beat.
Pour into a baking pan lined with aluminum foil. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Take out of the oven and let the brownies cool.
Beat the eggs and the sugar for 5 minutes. Place this mixture over a bain marie, stirring constantly for 2 to 3 minutes until it thickens.
Add the chocolate and cook for 3 more minutes.
Pour this mixture into another bowl and let it cool. Add the butter and beat using the electric mixer. The frosting should be creamy.
Spread the frosting over the brownies and sprinkle with mixed nuts.

title: chicken sausage wrapped in cabbage
directions: Wash the cabbage leaves and cut the hard center.
Blanch in boiling salted water and drain.
Place the cabbage leaves on the work surface one by one and carefully roll around the sausages.
Secure the cabbage using toothpicks or skewers.
In a large pan with a drizzle of olive oil, saute the chopped onion with the bay leaf.
Add the chopped tomatoes and the tomato pulp.Leave to braise for a little while.
Add the sausages and season with salt salt.
Cover and cook in moderate heat.
Add water or broth as needed.
Serve hot with homemade mashed potatoes.

title: chicken soup
directions: In a large pot, add the water, chicken, giblets, leek, and the chicken stock cube.
Simmer on medium heat until the chicken is cooked.
Remove the chicken and let cool. Shred the chicken.
Turn the heat on again and add the potatos and carrots.
Season with salt and cook until the vegetables are done.
Remove from heat.
Add the shredded chicken and couscous and cover.
The couscous will cook in the hot broth.
Stir just so the couscous does not sink to the bottom. Serve warm, drizzled with lemon.
Garnish with mint.

title: homemade rosemary butter
directions: Place all the ingredients in a bowl, except the rosemary flowers.
Whisk together until the cream separates, and the butter forms a ball and sticks to the whisks, leaving the liquid in the bowl.
Leave to drain over a colander and bowl.
Line a rectangular dish with parchment paper. (Or any other shaped dish-the butter will take the same shape as the dish.)
Place the butter into the dish and press down into the sides to completely fill the dish.
Just before serving, add the rosemary flowers on the top.
Serve with fresh bread.
Store in the refrigerator and use up quickly.

title: tiger prawn stir-fry
directions: Cook egg noodles until al dente. Drain and rinse under cold water to cool.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a wok or large frying pan. Add red pepper and stir-fry for 1-2 mins, until softened. Add garlic, ginger, baby corn, water chestnuts and bok choy. Stir-fry for 3-4 mins. Add prawns and sweet and sour sauce. Season. Add stock and cook over medium heat for 5 mins, stirring, until sauce has thickened.
Add noodles and toss to combine. Transfer to warmed serving plates. Sprinkle with sliced greens onions and serve with lemon wedges.

title: spicy red fruit jelly
directions: Cut the fruit into small pieces.
Arrange them by layers in glasses.
Heat the apple juice.
Add the vanilla bean, split in two, star anise, and 3 pinches (or less to taste) of cinnamon.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat, cover to let infuse for about 10 minutes.
Scrape the inside of the vanilla pod, and remove the star anise.
Add the agar-agar, fructose, and heat over high heat. Boil for about 30 seconds.
Remove from heat and pour into glasses.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: vegetable fried rice
directions: Cook rice in boiling water for 35 mins, or until tender. Rinse under cold water. Drain.

Meanwhile, heat a large wok over medium-high heat. Add 1 tsp oil and swirl to coat wok. Add eggs and swirl wok to make a thin omelette. Cook for 30 seconds, or until just set. Slide out onto a clean cutting board, roll up tightly and cut into strips.

Wipe out wok and add remaining oil. Stir-fry carrots and red onion for 4 mins, or until just tender. Add cabbage and stir-fry for 2 mins, or until wilted. Add garlic, ginger and 1 green onion. Stir-fry until fragrant. Add rice and soy sauce. Stir-fry until hot.
Serve rice topped with omelette, chili and remaining green onion.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Mix potato, chocolate, egg yolks, salt and honey.
Beat the white. Mix into the potato mixture.
Bake until 40 minutes.

title: chili beef cornbread
directions: Set oven at 350. pour oil or bacon dripping in a 9x13-3qt baking dish.
Place baking dish in the oven and let it get hot, not burning hot.
Add flour and cornmeal in a bowl and mix together. Add milk and blend together.
adding eggs and mix together very well. add the butter stir into the mixture. if the mixture to thick add more milk until smooth. add shredded cheese and blend very well.
Pour halve cornbread mixture in baking dish with hot oil or bacon dripping. Set aside

In a large skillet add ground beef cook until meat is done and crumbly drain excess grease and add onion, peppers, and garlic and cook until vegetables are transparent add corn and rotel tomatoes. add spices and simmer for five minutes. taste for profession adding more spices to your taste bubs.
Cornbread mixture is waiting, so add half meat mixture on top of half cornbread mixture in the baking dish evenly about 1/2 inch thick from ends to center.

Add cheese evenly over the meat mixture and add half wolf brand chili mixture on top of cheese.. pour the remaining cornbread mixture on top of cheese and add meat mixture. then add wolf brand chili mixture and place in oven 25 mins.take out oven and place shredded cheese to melt on top.

title: banana cream cheese
directions: For crust, bake 3 tablespoons powdered sugar, flour and butter in 10 x 13 inch pan until brown.
Add sliced bananas when crust is cooled.
Add cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar, Cool Whip, vanilla pudding and milk.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable noodle stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in a wok or large frying pan over high heat. Stir-fry onion, carrot, pepper, pak choy, mushrooms and garlic for 3-4 mins, until tender. Add noodles, kecap manis and soy sauce. Stir-fry for 1-2 mins, until heated through.
Sprinkle with peanuts, spring onion and chili. Drizzle with soy sauce.

title: nua cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 170 degrees Celsius.
Add 1 egg, 500 milliliters of milk, 120 grams of sugar, 60 grams of flour, and 1 teaspoon vanilla, and a small amount of lemon zest in a bowl. Mix well using an electric mixer on low speed.
Pour the mixture into a saucepan and cook it on low heat stirring continuously until it becomes a thick cream.
Allow the cream to cool and melt the two chocolates using a double boiler or in the microwave.
Once the cream has cooled, divide it into two bowls.
Add the melted chocolate to one of the bowls. Stir it well until it is blended well.
Beat the remaining and sugar in a bowl using an electric mixer on low speed.
Add a small amount of lemon zest and remaining vanilla and continue mixing.
Slowly pour the oil and continue mixing.
Add the remaining milk and mix for a few seconds.
Add the flour sifted with the baking powder and combine all the ingredients until completely incorporated.
Lightly oil and flour a 9-inch cake pan. Pour the batter into the pan.
Add spoonfuls of plain cream alternating with spoonfuls of chocolate cream atop the cake's surface.
Bake the cake for 45 minutes. Allow the cake to cool and serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Shape small balls with dough.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Place dough balls on the baking sheet and use a fork to press and slightly flatten.
Bake in preheated oven for 20-25 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: gluten free and dairy free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Grind desiccated coconut in the blender to make a vert fine flour, sieve.
Gind potato flakes in the blender if you cannot find potato flour, this will give you fine flour.
Measure the rest of the dry ingredients and blend together and lastly sieve. Set aside.
Beat butter in a mixing with beater attachment. Beat for 2-3 minutes at medium speed.
Add the brown sugar and continue beating for another 1-2 minutes until light and creamy.
Add eggs one at a time and continue mixing at slow speed, mix until well combined.
Add vanilla and mix again for 1 minute.
Add all of the dry ingredients and continue mixing on the lowest speed until dough comes together.
Add half of the dark chocolate chips and continue to mix of 1 minute until all of the chips are incorporated evenly on the dough.
Using a small ice cream scooper, scoop dough this will weigh around 30 grams to 32 grams.
Roll the dough in your palm to make a better round shape.
Add few more dark chocolate chips on top and lightly flatten the ball.
Place the dough into a lined baking tray and place them 2 to 3 inches apart from each other.
Bake them in preheated (18C) oven for 9 to 10 minutes. or until the sides of the cookie have a light brown color and bottom have light golden brown color.
Cool on wire racks.
Store on closed dry container.

title: super easy chocolate tart
directions: Chop the wafer completely in a food processor, until it looks like sand. Add the softened butter or margarine, and mix very well. Line the bottom of a pie plate. Alternatively, use a spring pan.
Place in a saucepan, the milk, cream, and a pinch of salt, and bring to boil. When almost boiling, remove from the heat, add the chocolate broken into pieces, and let it melt, stirring occasionally.
When the chocolates have melted, add the cereal, and mix very well. Pour this mixture on top of the ground wafers in the pie pan, and refrigerate for a few hours. Serve very cold.

title: butter cookie twists
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Line a baking tray with parchment paper.
Cream the butter and sugar together until lighter in color.
Add the vanilla extract and egg white.
Blend again.
Beat with the flour and sea salt little by little until you have a dough that is soft but not sticky.
You may use more or less than 250 grams of flour to achieve this consistency.
Pull off sections of the dough about a tablespoon in size.
Roll each section out into a 15-centimeter-long tube.
Fold the dough tube in half and twist it upon itself.
Set upon the baking tray, leaving at least 3 centimeters between each cookie.
Bake about 13 minutes until just turning golden.
Once cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: baked beans, prepared without a pressure cooker
directions: Wash the beans under running water and then add them in a large pot.
Add the coriander, garlic, coriander, oil, and water. Mix well.
Cook on medium-high heat and cover the pot with a lid.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to low heat and cook for 3 hours over low heat.
After 2 hours, add another liter of hot water to the beans.
Cook the beans until they are soft. Add salt and cook for another 10 minutes.
Serve the beans with tortillas and grated cheese.

title: molotov with sweet egg icing
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Molotof Preparation:
Grease a bundt pan, but do not flour. Set aside.
In a large bowl, place the egg whites with a pinch of fine salt and beat to stiff peaks.
Continue beating and add the sugar little by little until the mixture has a very firm meringue consistency.
Spoon the egg white mixture into the bundt pan. Tap the pan against a hard surface to burst any air bubbles that might have formed.
Bake for 11 minutes (1 minute per egg white).
When the time is up, turn off the oven, and leave the molotof inside the oven for 30 minutes. Never open the oven door.
After 30 minutes, open the oven door, but leave the molotof inside for another 30 minutes. Avoid sudden temperature changes, such as open windows or doors, which may cause a cold draft.
Unmold into a large dish.
For the topping:
In a saucepan, whisk the eggs.
Add the sugar and whisk some more.
Bring to simmer over medium heat, stirring constantly with the whisk until the mixture begins to thicken.
Remove the pan from the heat and immediately pour the mixture into another container to cool.
When it is almost cold, spread the icing on the molotof and sprinkle with nuts.
Cool before serving.

title: layered bean dip
directions: On a large platter place refried beans and spread out evenly; add taco seasoning to sour cream and spread mixture over beans.
Add avocados as next layer, then follow with shredded lettuce, tomato salsa, cheese and ripe olives. Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: turkey and cheese "mouse" burgers
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan and sear turkeys fillets for about 3 mins on each side until golden and cooked through. Cover and rest for 5 mins.

To make the mice, arrange most cucumber slices in two small stacks on a plate. Top with turkey fillets, lettuce and remaining cucumber slices. Place a mini Edam cheese on top. For the heads, take a slice off the base of each radish. Cut removed portion in 1/2 then make 2 small slits in the top of each radish and insert halved slices for "ears." Attach cloves for "eyes" and a little lettuce for "mouths." Place 1 head on top of each body and garnish plate with extra 2 heads. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 150 degrees Celsius.
In a bowl, mix together the butter, granulated sugar, vanilla extract, melted chocolate, and egg.
Separately, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and a pinch of salt.
Beat the two mixtures together until combined.
Roll the dough into a tube shape and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 1 hour until firm.
Cut the tube into 2-centimeter rounds and place the rounds on a baking tray, making sure to leave room between cookies (as they will spread out while baking).
Bake for 20 minutes, then set aside to cool completely.
For the filling, beat together the butter, powdered sugar, granulated sugar, vanilla extract, milk, and pinch of salt.
Fill a piping bag and pipe the filling onto the top of one cookie. Top with a second cookie to make a sandwich.

title: coq au vin
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Place garlic, bay leaves, thyme, parsley stalks and peppercorns on muslin or cheesecloth and tie with kitchen string to form a bouquet garni.

Heat half the oil and butter in a Dutch oven on medium-high heat. Add onion, mushrooms, celery and bacon and cook for 15 mins, stirring occasionally. Add brandy and scrape bottom of pan with wooden spoon to deglaze. Cook until reduced by half. Transfer to bowl and set aside.

Heat remaining oil and butter in the same pan on medium-high heat. Season chicken with salt and black pepper. Cook chicken, skin-side down, until golden (you may need to do this in batches). Transfer to bowl with mushrooms.

Add flour to fats and juices in pan and cook, stirring, for 1-2 mins. Add wine, stock and mustard and stir well. Return chicken and mushroom mixture to pan. Add carrots, potatoes and bouquet garni. Bring to a simmer.

Transfer to oven and cook, uncovered, for 2 hours, or until chicken is tender and falling off the bone. Remove from oven and skim off any excess fat. Discard bouquet garni. Garnish with parsley leaves and serve with crusty baguette.

title: pork chops with rosemary potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F.
Place pork chops in a glass dish. Mix wine, lemon peel and juice, oil, honey and spices in a small bowl. Pour over pork chops. Cover. Refrigerate 30 mins, turning once, to marinate.
Meanwhile, for the rosemary potatoes, place potatoes in a baking pan. Toss with oil, rosemary and garlic. Season to taste. Bake 40-45 mins, turning once, until golden and crisp.

After potatoes have cooked for 30 mins, melt butter in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add pork chops and apples, brushing well with marinade. Fry 10-15 mins, turning and basting, until cooked through. Add sage; cook 1-2 mins.
Serve pork chops with drizzled pan juices, apples, potatoes and lemon wedges.

title: spicy sausage and bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.

Heat oil in a Dutch oven. Saute sausages for 6-7 mins, until browned. Add onions and chili. Cook for 5 mins, until softened. Add tomatoes, beans, tomato puree, chili powder and cumin. Bring to a boil and season. Transfer to oven and bake for 30 mins.
Serve with spoonfuls of sour cream. Garnish with fresh cilantro.

title: sausage and tortellini soup
directions: Saute onions, garlic and carrots in olive oil until onions are soft and carrots are beginning to soften (they will continue to cook as the soup simmers.).
Add in diced sausage and saute for a few minutes. Add in tomatoes, beef consomme, water. Add in spices. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Ten minutes before it is done add in diced zucchini and tortellini and cook until tortellini is tender.
Pour into bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan Cheese.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool cake 15 minutes.
Prick top with fork.
Pour condensed milk in the holes.
When cool, cover with bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator. (May substitute strawberries or pineapple.)
This recipe may be doubled.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thinly slice the apple horizontally. Pour a few drops of lime on the apple to prevent it from browning.
Sprinkle the sugar on top of the apple.
Use a blowtorch to caramelize the sugar.
Use a fork to crush the blackberries and blueberries.
Place the crushed berries on top of the apple.
Sprinkle with honey.

title: calamari-lemon pasta
directions: Cut 1 lemon half into very thin (about 1/10-inch) half-moon slices. (Reserve the other half for another use.)
Cut the squid tubes into thin rings.

Heat a large, deep skillet over medium-high heat and add 2 tablespoons of oil. Add half the squid and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until just cooked through, 3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl. Add 1 tablespoon of oil and cook the remaining half of the squid. Transfer to the same bowl-do not wipe out the skillet.
Reduce the heat to medium and add 2 more tablespoons of oil. Add the onion and bell pepper and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until tender and browned in places, 3 minutes.
Add the garlic, chile flakes, and about 2/3 of the lemon slices to the pan and cook, scraping up browned bits, until softened, 2 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook the linguine in boiling, salted water until al dente, 9-10 minutes. Reserve 1 cup pasta water.

Add the linguine to the skillet along with 1/2 cup pasta water. Cook, tossing to combine and adding more pasta water as needed, 2 minutes. Add the cooked squid and 1/4 cup herbs and stir to combine, 1 minute.
Divide the pasta among 4 bowls and drizzle generously with olive oil. Garnish with the remaining lemon halves and chopped herbs and serve right away.

title: yellow cake
directions: preheat your oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch round cake pan.
With an electric mixer on high, beat sugar, eggs, & vanilla for one minute to thicken.
On low speed add remaining ingredients (in the order listed) but do not over-mix. This should take less than a minute.
Pour into pan and bake for 25-30 minutes until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: beer dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let set overnight.
Serve with bread chunks.

title: chopped salad with lemon
directions: Place the chopped onion in a bowl and then add the lemon zest and lemon juice. Allow the onions to sit in the juice for 2 minutes.
Peel the cucumber, remove the seeds and chop it and place into another bowl.
Remove the seeds from the tomato and cut it into small cubes. Add it to the bowl with the cucumber.
Add oil, and a pinch of salt and black pepper to the onions and mix well.
Add the tomato, cucumber, spinach and cheese to the onions and mix well.

title: lazy day beef & vegetable soup
directions: Combine beef, broth, chickpeas, tomatoes, water, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper in 4-1/2 to 5-1/2-quart slow cooker; toss to coat well. Cover and cook on HIGH 5 hours or on LOW 8 hours. (No stirring is necessary during cooking.)

Stir in mixed vegetables and pasta. Continue cooking, covered, 1 hour or until beef and pasta are tender. Season with salt and pepper, as desired. Stir well before serving. Serve with cheese, if desired.

title: maryland crab cake sandwiches
directions: Combine 1/4 cup Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Real Mayonnaise, 1/2 teaspoon seafood seasoning and 1 teaspoon lemon juice in small bowl; reserve.

Combine remaining 1/4 cup Mayonnaise, 1 teaspoon seafood seasoning, 1 teaspoon lemon juice, egg, Worcestershire sauce and 1 cup cracker crumbs in large bowl. Gently stir in crabmeat; shape into 4 patties.
Evenly coat patties with remaining 1/2 cup cracker crumbs. Arrange on prepared baking sheet. Bake, turning once, 16 minutes or until golden brown and thoroughly cooked.
Evenly spread reserved mayonnaise mixture on both sides of buns, then top with lettuce and crabcakes.
Preheat oven to 425°. Line baking sheet with aluminum foil, then spray with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.

title: raspberry and chocolate meringue pies
directions: For the pie crust, crush the chocolate cookies to a powder, combine with the melted butter and mix well. Let cool.

To make the raspberry curd, place the raspberries, sugar, lemon juice and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat and let simmer for about 5 minutes. Remove from the heat then grind the mixture with a hand blender or a blender. Pass the mixture through a sieve to get a homogeneous, lump-free liquid. Put it back in the saucepan, add the egg yolks and the cornstarch and stir well. Bring it to a boil for about 1 minute, or until it starts thickening. Add a pinch of salt and the butter. Fold gently until it becomes smooth and creamy. Put it in the fridge for about 2 hours.

For the meringue, beat the egg whites very well in a kitchen mixer until stiff. In a small saucepan, bring the sugar and water to boil. Allow the sugar to dissolve and let simmer for about 5 minutes until a thick syrup is formed.
In the mixer with the mixer switched on, slowly add the syrup to the whites and whisk until you get a creamy, firm and shiny meringue texture.

Place the chocolate cookie mixture in the bottom of ramekins or small bowls. Press using a spoon. Place the raspberry curd on top of it. Place the meringue in a pastry bag and squeeze out the meringue in a swirl on top of the dessert.
Give a caramelized touch to the meringue with a blowtorch so that it becomes golden. Serve immediately or store in the fridge.

title: individual turkey and vegetable pies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a 12-cup muffin pan. Line with pastry rounds, pressing dough into recesses of pan.

Combine turkey, breadcrumbs, vegetables, chili sauce, cilantro, egg, oil and chili flakes. Season then distribute between pie shells. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 15-20 mins, until lightly browned and cooked through.

title: coconut chicken soup
directions: Combine the crumbled stock cubes with 5 cups of water in a large, heavy-based pot over a moderate heat. Bring to a boil, then add the chicken and coconut milk. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 mins.
Add the carrot and celery to the soup and simmer for 5 mins, or until the chicken is cooked through. Stir in the lime juice, cumin and ground coriander and simmer for 2 mins or until fragrant.
Divide the soup among serving bowls, sprinkle with cilantro and serve with warmed naan bread.

title: pork kebabs with radish salad
directions: Mix the beer, 2 tbsp of the oil, rosemary and jam in a large bowl. Add the pork and toss to coat well. Cover and refrigerate for about 2 hours to marinate.

Mix 1/3 of the arugula, cream, mustard, remaining 3 tbsp of oil and the vinegar in a food processor or blender. Puree until smooth. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Toast the pine nuts and pumpkin seeds in a dry skillet until lightly browned. Remove from the pan and set aside cool.

Remove the meat from the marinade and thread onto 8-10 skewers, alternating with the peppers, onions and bay leaves. Season with salt. Broil or grill the skewers for about 10 mins, turning and basting occasionally with the marinade.
Toss the radishes, greens onions, remaining arugula, lettuce, pine nuts and pumpkin seeds with the arugula vinaigrette. Serve with the skewers, garnished with the reserved rosemary.

title: perfect grilled pork loin chops
directions: Season both sides of chops with salt and pepper on both sides and allow to rest on counter for 15-30 minutes.
Preheat grill and season grill with towel dipped in vegetable oil (use tongs for safety). Just before grilling, squeeze lime juice on both sides of the chops, and then brush with vegetable oil.

Grill the chops on medium-high direct heat until lightly charred on the outside, but juicy and pink on the inside, about 4 minutes per side or until the internal temperature reaches 145 degree F. Remove chops from grill and let rest a full 5 minutes before serving.

title: simple & delicious grilled pork loin
directions: Place sliced pork in a bowl and let marinade in the refrigerator for half an hour or longer.

Heat a griddle or cast iron frying pan and place the pork on the hot griddle or frying pan and let the pork become a beautiful golden color. The pork will not take long to cook since it is sliced very thin.

title: mini vegan pumpkin-glazed doughnuts
directions: First, rinse and drain the kidney beans and place them in your KitchenAid(R) Diamond Blender. Add the soy milk, coconut sugar and cocoa powder and blend together on the Mix (3) setting.

Then, transfer the mixture to the largest mixing bowl part of the KitchenAid(R) 3pc Ceramic Mixing Bowl Set and stir in the flour, baking powder and vanilla until the dough comes together smoothly and thoroughly mixed. If it seems a little dry, add a little more soy milk or a tablespoon or two of coconut or vegetable oil.

Spoon a couple of tablespoons of dough into your KitchenAid(R) Mini Doughnut Pans (fill to the top and smooth). This recipe makes approximately 16-18 doughnuts, so you'll need at least 2 Mini Doughnut Pans or make them in 3 batches.

Preheat your KitchenAid(R) Convection Countertop Oven on 350° F. Bake the doughnuts in your preheated Countertop Oven for 10 minutes. Let them cool for a couple of minutes in the Mini Doughnut Pan, then remove and place them on a cooling rack while you make the Salted Caramel Pumpkin Spice Glaze.

To make the doughnut glaze, simply place all your ingredients (coconut sugar, coconut cream, vanilla extract, Himalayan pink sea salt, pumpkin puree and pumpkin spice) in a saucepan from a KitchenAid(R) 7-Ply Stainless Steel 10-Piece Set over medium-high heat.

Bring to a rolling boil, and continuously whisk for about 10 minutes until the glaze starts to thicken, caramelize, and turn a dark brown color (be careful to constantly watch and stir, and not let the caramel burn - reducing heat to medium-low if needed). Let the glaze cool to the side for a few minutes after it's done to allow it to thicken a little more.

Spoon the glaze over the doughnuts on a baking sheet covered in foil or parchment paper and garnish with flaky sea salt. You can also top the doughnuts with some crushed nuts if you'd like (hazelnuts or pecans would be amazing!).

Note: The glaze can be made ahead of time and will keep in the refrigerator for up to 1 week. It can also be reheated in the microwave. Or let it come to room temperature before glazing the mini doughnuts.

title: fried codfish - actifry recipe
directions: Place the chopped onion and garlic cloves In the Actifry.
Drizzle with a little bit of olive oil, set the Actifry for 2 minutes and cook.
Thaw, drain, and cut the codfish into small pieces, and add to the Actifry.
Cook for 8 minutes.
Peel the potatoes and cut them into small cubes.
When the codfish is ready, remove and set aside.
Put the potatoes in the actifry (without washing the container) season with salt, garlic powder, and paprika.
Sprinkle with olive oil and cook for 20 minutes.
Boil the eggs in a pot with salted water.
Place the codfish container on top of the pot to keep it warm.
When the potatoes are done, add the cod and cook for 2 or 3 more minutes.
Place on a serving plate and garnish with the chopped boiled eggs and olives.

title: homemade dried tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry the tomatoes. Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove the seeds and place face down to drain on a rack or in a colander for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees Fahrenheit.
Spread the tomatoes in a baking pan, avoid overlapping, and sprinkle with a bit of sugar and salt.
Bake from 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
After that, turn over, and bake again from 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
The tomatoes will be dry and creased. If not done, bake anther 30 minutes.
Once they're dry, let cool.
Place the tomatoes in a clean, dry jar, pressing them in a little bit.
Add spices between layers (optional).
Once the jar is full, pour in olive oil until tomatoes are submerged.
If necessary, the day after, add a bit more: tomatoes must always be in contact with oil for preservation.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix the dry ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well with your hands.
Make balls the size of walnuts.
Place the cookies separated on a board (that can go to the oven) lined with parchment paper (no need to grease).
Take to a preheated oven at 350°F and then lower to 320°F and bake about 20 minutes.
Remove, sprinkle with cinnamon and let cool down.

title: peach pineapple jam
directions: Mix pectin with 1 cup sugar, stir into peaches, orange and pineapple.
Heat to boiling.
Add sugar all at once, bring back to a boil and boil one minute.
Skim and pour into clean, sterilized canning jars.
Process in a boiling water bath 10 minutes.
If pectin is not available, combine fruit and sugar in pan, cook until mixture is thick and comes off spoon in sheets.

title: bacon, ham, and carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
In a frying pan with a drizzle of olive oil, brown the chopped onion and the bacon. Remove from heat, and drain the grease.
In a bowl, beat the eggs, yogurt, and oil. Add cheese, grated carrot, strips of ham, onion and bacon.
Gradually, add the flour to the egg mixture, season with salt, herbs, and ground pepper.
Mix well, and partially fill muffin or cupcake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: fruit nougat
directions: Stone the dates, cut the stems off the figs, stone the raisins (or use seedless raisins), and shell the walnuts; put all the fruit and nuts through the meat chopper, roll out thin on a board sprinkled with powdered sugar, and cut into squares.
These are delicious dipped in melted sweet chocolate.

title: lamb chops with baba ghanoush
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Place eggplant and garlic cloves in a baking pan and toss with olive oil. Bake for 20-25 mins, until tender. Allow to cool slightly.

To make the baba ghanoush, peel the garlic and place in a food processor with the eggplant, lemon juice, tahini, 1 tbsp olive oil and ground cumin and coriander. Season to taste. Process until smooth.
In the same baking dish, toss tomatoes with 2 tbsp olive oil. Bake for 10 mins, until skins begin to split.
Preheat a grill on medium. Lightly oil the grill and cook lamb chops for 5-10 mins each side, or until cooked to taste.
Serve chops topped with spoonfuls of baba ghanoush, potato slices and steamed beans. Accompany with lemon wedges.

title: toffee chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, oil, sugar and powdered sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Beat in egg and vanilla extract.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Beat in chocolate chips and toffee bits.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough into 48 pieces; roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Dip a flat bottomed drinking glass into sugar and gently flatten each cookie.
Bake in preheated 350°F oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges of cookies are lightly browned.
Immediately remove from baking sheets and cool on racks.

title: oven-roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine all ingredients until evenly coated in 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring once, 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: max & erma's stuffed potato soup
directions: Place heavy stockpot over med-high heat, add diced bacon. Cook, stirring frequently, until bacon is brown, 5-7 minutes.... pull out & drain half of it and set aside.
Immediately add onions and celery and saute until soft, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and add flour to veggies and bacon. Cook over low for 5 minutes to cook out the raw flour taste.
Add chicken broth and potato cubes. Increase heat to med-high and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat to medium and cook for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add half-and-half, white and black pepper and salt and simmer for 5 minutes more.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Taste and adjust seasonings.
Garnish with crisp bacon, grated cheese and diced green onions if desired.

title: crispy polenta, pepper and walnut salad
directions: Oil a 12x8 inch rimmed baking dish.

Bring 4 cups water to a boil. Gradually stir in polenta. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring, for about 10 mins, or until polenta thickens. Stir in cheese until melted. Transfer to prepared pan, smooth surface and chill for 1 hour, or until firm.
Turn polenta out onto a cutting board and cut into 1/3 inch cubes. Heat oil in a large frying pan. Cook polenta until browned lightly. Toss with remaining ingredients.
Meanwhile, to make the walnut dressing, whisk together all ingredients. Season. Add to salad and toss to combine.

title: spare ribs roasted with garlic & red pepper
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees:
Cut the rack of spare ribs between the bones into single ribs.

Place them in a roasting pan and add the olive oil, garlic, bay leaves and red pepper flakes. Pour in the stock and roast, until the liquid is almost completely evaporated and the ribs are golden brown. About 2 hours.

title: warm philly mexican spread
directions: Heat grill to medium heat.
Combine tomatoes, garlic and dressing.
Place cream cheese on sheet of heavy-duty foil; top with tomato mixture and shredded cheese. Place on grill grate.
Grill 8 to 10 min. or until shredded cheese is melted and cream cheese is softened but still holds its shape. Sprinkle with cilantro. Serve with crackers.

title: sweet potato rosti with smoked salmon and avocado
directions: Add the egg to a medium sized bowl and add the grated sweet potato, salt, paprika and red onion.
Add 1/2 tsp coconut oil to a fry pan and heat on medium heat. Spoon in the rosti mixture and press down to form a pancake. Fry for a few minutes each side until golden brown and cooked through.
Remove the rosti from the pan. Serve topped with smoked salmon, green leaves, zucchini/snow peas and avocado mixture. Top with poached egg if desired.

title: sautéed chicken with vegetables and almonds
directions: Sprinkle the bottom of a wok with a little olive oil and add 1/2 chicken stock cube.
Cut the chicken breasts into small pieces and place in wok. Season with a little salt and sprinkle with the lemon juice.
While the chicken cooks, dice the red pepper and onion and cut the leek into thin slices.
When the chicken begins to brown, add the prepared vegetables and almonds. Sprinkle with soy sauce and stir to combine for about 5 minutes.
Serve with white rice.

title: english muffins
directions: Pour the warm water, yeast, sugar, salt, egg, half of the regular flour, and all of the whole wheat flour into a bowl and mix with an electric mixer or wooden spoon.
Once the mixture has formed into a ball of dough, cover the bowl with plastic wrap and let it sit for 1 hour.
Once the hour has passed, add the rest of the flour and the butter into the bowl and stir everything with an electric mixer until the dough becomes soft and elastic.
Allow the dough to sit for another hour.
Cover a table or large tray with flour and then place the dough on the surface. Begin kneading the dough for a few seconds and then let the dough sit for another 30-45 minutes.
Heat up a pan on the stove over low-medium heat. Add the vegetable oil and place medium sized, round portions of dough in the pan.
Cook the loaves for 2 minutes on each side, then begin cooking each side in 4 minute intervals. If the dough appears to need more time, cook each side for another 4 minutes.
Place the rolls on a plate and let them cool before serving.

title: savory chorizo and walnut cookies
directions: In a skillet, brown the chopped nuts for 3 to 4 minutes. Watch carefully. Let cool.
Mix flour, yeast, salt, pepper, nuts, and chorizo.
In a bowl, mix the butter and the beaten egg. Add to the flour mixture.
Make a ball of dough using your fingers.
Form 18 small balls of dough about the size of a walnut.
Arrange them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, and press lightly with the palm of your hand.
Put in the freezer for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Bake for about 20 minutes.
Set them aside for 5 minutes before cooling on a tray.

title: lemon blueberry ice cream floats
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and lemon zest. Rub sugar and lemon zest together with your fingers until fragrant. Stir in the lemon juice, heavy cream, and salt. Whisk until smooth.
Cover the mixture and chill in the refrigerator for at least one hour, can be chilled overnight.

To churn the ice cream, use the KitchenAid(R) Ice Cream Maker Attachment. Assemble and engage freeze bowl, dasher, and drive assembly as directed in the attachment instructions. Turn to stir. Pour mixture into freeze bowl. Continue on Stir for 15-20 minutes or until desired consistency. Transfer ice cream to an airtight container and freeze until completely solid.

To make the blueberry syrup, combine blueberries, water, sugar, and fresh lemon juice in a medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves, about 3-5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Strain and place mixture in the refrigerator to chill.
Use the KitchenAid(R) Sparkling Beverage Maker and make one bottle of soda water, according to manufacturer's instructions.

To assemble the floats, put two scoops of lemon ice cream in a tall float glass. Add 1/4 cup blueberry syrup to each glass. Pour soda water over the ice cream. Garnish with fresh blueberries and mint, if desired. Serve immediately.

title: beef crepes
directions: Brown beef in oil. Stir in the onions and cook until they start to change color. Add mushrooms and garlic and cook until liquid has evaporated.

Season with salt, pepper and a pinch nutmeg Add the tomatoes and the bell peppers and cook stirring 3 minutes. Turn down heat, cover pan and simmer45 minutes to 1 hour, adding a little water if it starts to dry out. Add the olives and the parsley , bring to a boil and turn off heat. Place about 1 tbs of the filling into each crepe, roll them up and place them into a buttered baking dish. Cover with tomatosauce and bechamel. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese Bake at 350 for 25 minutes or unt

title: mushroom soup casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Return to pan.
Stir in soup, milk, mushrooms, onion, sour cream and noodles; simmer, covered for 5-8 minutes

title: ricotta, vanilla and lemon cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 180C.
Beat the ricotta cheese with the sugar, a pinch of salt, the lemon extract, the grated peel of 1 lemon, and the vanilla seeds.
Add the egg.
Incorporate the flour; the mixture should be smooth and uniform in consistency.
Cut the dough into pieces and shape into long links, then braid the links or shape them into rings.
Coat the cookies with granulated sugar and place them on a wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Bake the cookies for approximately 20 minutes.
Remove the cookies from the oven and cool on a wire rack.

title: milk chocolate pots
directions: Place cream and coffee in a small saucepan on medium heat. Bring almost to a boil, stirring to dissolve coffee. Remove from heat. Stir in liqueur and vanilla.
Place chopped chocolate in a medium bowl. Pour cream mixture over and stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.

Whisk in egg yolks and butter, until smooth. Cool for 2-3 mins. Stirring in 3/4 of the chopped candy bar. Spoon mixture evenly into six 1/4-cup ramekins or espresso cups. Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Top with remaining chopped candy bar and slivered pistachios. Serve with orange wedges, if desired.

title: crepe suzette
directions: Sift flour into a large bowl. Stir in sugar and make a well in the center. In another bowl, combine milk, eggs and butter. Gradually pour milk mixture into the well in the flour mixture and whisk until smooth. Chill 30 minutes.
Melt 1 tbsp butter in an 8 inch crepe pan on medium heat. Pour in batter, swirling to coat base. Cook 1-2 minutes, until underside is golden. Turn and cook a further 1 minute.
Transfer to a plate. Repeat with remaining batter, adding extra butter to pan as required.

To make sauce, combine sugar, juices and liqueur in a frying pan on medium, stirring until sugar dissolves. Increase heat to high and boil 4-5 minutes until thick and syrupy. Reduce heat to low and whisk in butter. Add orange segments and heat through gently, stirring.
Fold crepes into quarters and arrange on serving plates. Spoon sauce over and accompany with ice cream.

title: roast chicken and mushroom spaghetti
directions: If the chicken and juices are very cold, heat for 2 minutes in the microwave. This will make it easier to shred the meat from the bones.
Remove the bones by hand and shred the chicken. Set aside.
Finely slice the onions and mushrooms. Set aside.
Heat a drizzle of oil in a heavy-bottomed pan. Add the onion and mushrooms and fry gently until soft.
Add the chicken and stir in the meat juices. Cook gently for 5 minutes.
Add the chili powder and cream. Adjust the seasoning and continue to cook for a few more minutes.
Bring to the boil 1 1/2 liter of water with a pinch of salt. Add the spaghetti and cook for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Chop the coriander and set aside.
Serve the pasta, covered with sauce and sprinkled with coriander.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Melt the dark chocolate and the butter over a double boiler on low heat.
Once melted, place the mixture in a bowl to cool slightly.
In the meantime, sift the flour with the baking powder, the cocoa, and a pinch of salt.
Add the eggs to the melted chocolate mixture.
Add the sugar and stir quickly.
Add the dry ingredients, a little at a time, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Add the chocolate chips, cover the bowl with plastic wrap, and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
After the dough has rested, shape it into walnut-sized balls and place them on a wax paper lined baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove the cookies from the oven and cool on a wire rack.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix condensed milk with cold water until it dissolves.
Pour in the instant vanilla pudding into the milk until it thickens.
Chill in the fridge for at least 4 hours. (Don't forget to cover).
After four hours, whip the heavy cream to peak.
Pour in the pudding into the cream, fold and mix evenly. Texture should be smooth.
Chill in the fridge for another 4 hours (or not, if you can't wait :P)
Use individual crystal cup or ramekin - and spread a little of the pudding in the bottom.
Alternately layer banana slices and wafers - with pudding in between each.
Repeat and end with pudding on top.
Garnish with a sprinkle of wafers, nuts, and grated chocolate.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on high heat. Saute onion and garlic 3-4 mins, until tender. Add tomatoes and spinach. Cook, stirring 1-2 mins, until spinach has wilted.
Reduce heat to low. Add cream cheese, chili sauce and chives. Cook, stirring, 2 mins until combined.
Spoon into a serving bowl. Sprinkle with paprika and serve warm with corn chips.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees. Place meat in large shallow baking pan. Place in oven and roast for 30 minutes.

Meanwhile, heat butter in skillet over moderately low heat, add mushrooms, cook until tender. Reduce oven temperature to 375 degrees. Remove suet from top of roast. Spoon mushrooms around meat, pour sherry over it. Salt and pepper if desired. Roast 20 minutes longer or until thermometer shows 140 degrees rare or 160 degrees for medium rare. Baste frequently.

title: vietnamese iced coffee
directions: Fill 4 glasses with ice cubes and pour in the coffee. Add 2 tbsp condensed milk to each glass, stir and serve.

title: "fruit salad" salad smoothie
directions: Combine everything in blender except ice and cinnamon.
With blender running, add ice cubes one at a time.
Divide Smoothie into 4 chilled glasses and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cranberry-almond biscotti
directions: Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 350 degrees F. Line baking sheet with parchment paper. Whisk flour, baking powder and salt together in small bowl.

Using a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, beat butter and sugar together at medium-high speed until light and fluffy. Reduce speed to low and add eggs one at a time, then add almonds, cranberries, orange zest, vanilla and almond extracts until combined, about 30 seconds, scraping down bowl as needed. Stir in flour mixture until just combined.

Halve dough and turn each portion onto prepared baking sheet. Using floured hands, quickly stretch each portion of dough into rough 12-inch-by-2-inch loaf, placing them about 3 inches apart. Pat each loaf to smooth it. Bake until loaves are golden and just beginning to crack on top, about 35 minutes, rotating baking sheet halfway through baking.

Let loaves cool for 10 minutes; reduce oven temperature to 325 degrees. Using a serrated knife, cut each loaf diagonally into 1/2-inch slices. Lay slices cut side up about 1/2 inch apart on baking sheet and return them to the oven. Bake until lightly golden on both sides, about 15 minutes, turning over each piece halfway through baking. Immediately transfer biscotti from baking sheet to wire rack and let cool completely.

title: rum raisin ice cream
directions: Soak the raisins in the rum for a few hours or the day before.
For the thermomix or food processor, use the flexible beater and the splash guard lid.
Put the sugar and milk powder in the bowl. Mix for 2 minutes at speed 3.
Gradually, pour the milk into the mixture on speed 3.
Add the egg yolk and the whipping cream.
Put it in the ice cream maker for about 15 minutes, then add the rum and raisin mixture and run for 5 more minutes more at speed 3.
Place in the freezer.

title: curried beef hand pies
directions: Place flour and salt into the bowl of your KitchenAid(R) Food Processor. Pulse a few times until the flour mixture is mixed. Add chilled shortening and butter to the food processor and pulse for about 30 to 60 seconds, until shortening and butter particles are the size of small peas.

While pulsing, stream in water 1 Tablespoon at a time. Pulse until ingredients are moistened and dough begins to form and pull away from the sides of the food processor. You may not use all of the water. Remove dough from food processor and divide in half. Mold each half into a circle and flatten. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerator for at least 15 minutes.

In a non-stick skillet or cast iron skillet, heat olive oil on medium for 1 to 2 minutes. Add onion and garlic and cook until onion is translucent. Add salt and pepper and ground beef. Break up the ground beef and cook for 4 to 5 minutes. Drain the cooked ground beef, if needed. Add potatoes and allow to cook for 5 to 8 minutes, mixing occasionally.

Add lemon juice, cayenne and curry powder. Mix well and cook for 2 to 4 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add peas, corn and cilantro. Cook until peas and corn are heated through. Add salt and pepper to taste. Remove pan from heat and allow filling to cool slightly.
Make the hand pies
Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Line two baking sheets with parchment paper or spray baking sheets lightly with non-stick cooking spray and set aside.

We're going to work with one pie pastry half at a time. Remove from the refrigerator. Take two pieces of parchment paper and place pie crust in between the two pieces. Using a rolling pin, roll to about a 1/8 inch thickness. Using a well-floured 4 1/2 to 5 inch cutter (or you can use a plastic lid or the opening of a plastic container), cut round circles. Place cut out pie crusts on the lined baking sheets. Roll the excess pie dough into a ball and flatten and wrap in plastic wrap and place back into the refrigerator and move onto the other half of the pie pastry. Repeat until all pie crusts have been cut.

Add about 2 Tablespoons beef & potato filling to each round (more if you're cutting the pie circles larger). It will feel like you're overfilling but you're not. Brush egg along one side of the circle. Fold in half and using your fingers, seal the pie. Using the tines of a fork, crimp the edges. Repeat and fill pies until there's no pie crust left. Brush the pies with the beaten egg. Bake hand pies for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove pies and allow to cool for at least 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Pies can be served as an appetizer or served with a salad and/or soup to make a meal.

title: moroccan chicken tagine
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook 8 minutes or until browned, turning once. Remove chicken from skillet

Stir onions into skillet; cook and stir on medium heat 5 minutes or until golden brown. Add roasted cinnamon, ginger, cumin, garlic powder, sea salt and saffron, if desired. Stir in tomatoes and honey. Return chicken to skillet. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in raisins; cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until chicken is cooked through
Serve with cooked couscous, if desired. Garnish with toasted slivered almonds and chopped fresh cilantro, if desired

title: westphalian chicken soup
directions: Simmer the bacon and onion in 2 cups water for about 1 hour. Add the green and white beans, herbs, potatoes, carrots, apples and pears to the bacon and onions, pour in the stock and simmer for about 30 mins. Add the sugar and vinegar and season and serve garnished with oregano.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Spray a large saucepan with olive oil. Heat on medium and saute garlic 2-3 mins. Add potatoes, leek, and bay leaves. Cook, stirring, for 2 mins.
Pour in stock. Bring to a boil on high. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 20-25 mins, until potatoes are tender. Remove bay leaves.
Puree mixture using a hand blender or food processor. Stir in milk. Reheat gently. Serve immediately, topped with chives and yogurt.

title: scrambled eggs with smoked salmon
directions: combine eggs and milk in a bowl, melt butter on skillet on low heat until it bubbles, then pour eggs in, stir continuously until it cooks, then pour half the parmesan in, and keep stirring. Turn off the heat, then stir in smoked salmon. Pepper to taste, and serve on toasted bread, top with remaining parmesan and chives.

title: chocolate peppermint cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners.

Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add peppermint extract. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour and cocoa powder together. Fold into batter, alternating with milk. Fold in chocolate. Distribute between paper liners and bake for 15-20 mins, until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

To decorate, roll out fondant on a clean work surface to 1/8 inch thick. Cut out 12 - 2 1/2 inch rounds. Brush tops of cupcakes with glucose. Top each with a fondant round. Brush underside of chocolates with glucose and press onto cupcakes.

title: crock pot red beans & rice
directions: Saute chopped onions & garlic in 1 Tablespoon olive oil in a skillet until soft.
Add seasonings to form a paste.
Add 2 cups of stock & bring to boil. Set aside.
In crock pot, add remaining olive oil & spread around bottom of pot with a paper towel.
Add rice, remaining stock, diced ham, andouille sausage, beans, & contents of skillet.
Stir well.
Cover the crock pot & cook on High for 6-7 hours.
Notes: Stir only once in the middle or not at all. I use a 7 quart crock pot for this recipe. In a pinch, I have used water instead of stock. Just add a little salt.

title: stuffed sausages with garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook sausages for 10-12 mins, turning frequently, until cooked through. Butterfly each sausage and spread mustard over top. Combine cheese, breadcrumbs, olives and parsley and spread over sausages. Sandwich back together and set aside.
Preheat broiler. Arrange sausages on a foil-lined tray. Broil for 4-5 mins, until sausages are heated through and cheese melts.
For the garlic mashed potatoes, cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 15-20 mins, until tender. Drain and mash with milk, butter and garlic.
Serve sausages with garlic mashed potatoes and sauteed cabbage and apple.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Place the milk and the sugar in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Add the chocolate and let it melt slowly.
Melt the butter in another saucepan and add the flour slowly to avoid lumps.
Add a little of the milk mixture and then remove the saucepan from the heat.
Stir with a spoon and return the saucepan to the heat once the milk mixture has been incorporated completely.
Stir continuously on the stove for 1 or 2 minutes and add the milk mixture gradually repeating these steps. The pudding will turn out creamy and uniform in consistency.
Wet a 1 liter silicone pudding mold with cold water and pour the pudding inside.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Remove the mold from the refrigerator, place the mold in hot water for a few seconds and turn the pudding out onto a serving platter.
Garnish with candied orange peel or strawberries, raspberries, or other fruit of your choice.

title: turmeric golden milk
directions: Mix all ingredients in small saucepan with a whisk until well blended.
Cook on medium-low heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Once complete - sip, enjoy and experience the benefits of turmeric milk!

title: watermelon a la mode
directions: Microwave caramel ice cream topping with marshmallows in microwave-safe bowl at HIGH 20 seconds; stir until smooth. Set aside.
Arrange watermelon on 4 dessert plates. Evenly top with Breyers(R) Grasshopper Pie Ice Cream, then drizzle with marshmallow mixture. Garnish, if desired, with blueberries and/or whipped cream.

title: baked apples with tequila
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Place the raisins, almonds, sugar and 2 tablespoons tequila in a bowl and mix well. Set aside for later use.
Fill the apples with the raisin and almond mixture.
Put the apples in a baking dish. If desired, cover the bottom of the dish with a layer of prunes and dates.
Add the butter to the baking dish. Add the apples.
In a bowl, mix the remaining tequila and honey. Drizzle the tequila mixture onto the apples.
Cove the dish with aluminum foil and place it in the oven for 45 minutes.
Take the skillet out of the oven, let it cool off for 5-10 minutes, cut, and serve.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Sesame seeds (optional) bimby put the cup of yeast, water, sugar, butter, salt and buttermilk and program 2min. 37 vel.2 Add the egg and then the flour and mix for 10 s. in Vel. 6. Select a program kneading for 2 min. Remove the dough and form small balls of equal size and then place them in a baking tray lined with parchment paper and let double in volume. Turn the oven to 170 °. With scissors make two cuts in a cross shape on the surface of the loaves . Brush with milk and sprinkle some sesame seeds and let levedem more. Bake for 12-15 min. until they win a golden brown tint.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Spread your favorite soft cheese on New York Style Garlic Bagel Crisps(R). Top with a peeled, boiled shrimp and a dollop of zesty cocktail sauce. Place a few on a platter and serve with lemon wedges. Get creative and add a sprig of dill or sprinkle on some Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 180°C (approximately 350°F).
In a bowl, add all ingredients and beat for 5 minutes with an electric mixer.
Pour batter in a greased and flour cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 50-60 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.
For the icing, combine all the ingredients in a saucepan and heat over low heat.
Stir until smooth and creamy. Let cool and frost cake.

title: double chocolate chip cookie sandwiches
directions: Evenly scoop Breyers(R) BLASTS! CHIPS AHOY!(R) Chocolate Chip Cookie Frozen Dairy Dessert onto 8 cookies, then top with remaining cookies, pressing gently and using knife to smooth sides. Roll sandwiches in chocolate chips. Serve immediately or freeze until ready to serve.

title: crispy chocolate waffles
directions: Combine the flour, butter, sugar, cocoa, eggs, and grated lemon peel.
Stir to a soft batter, if necessary add some flour.
Cook the waffles by using a waffle iron.
Serve with some nutella and sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: pork tenderloins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a small bowl, combine honey, vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Sprinkle tenderloin liberally with salt and pepper.
Coat tenderloin well with the sauce.
Place tenderloin in a shallow pan and roast for 20 - 25 minutes or until meat thermometer inserted registers 155 - 160 degrees.
If you want the tenderloin to keep its shape, you will need to truss it with kitchen string.
Slice to serve.

title: coconut creamed spinach
directions: Consume a raw leaf and raw coconut for your mouth to know all the layers of flavor
Gently warm olive oil in a pan, about ten seconds, and add spinach.
Let spinach gently wilt but don't allow any oil popping to occur
Spoon in coconut butter and let melt
Immediately Consume

title: scorpionfish pate
directions: Blend all of the ingredients together, except the 3 diced crab sticks, until a thick cream is formed.
Add the diced crab sticks.
Serve with toasted bread.

title: banana and raspberry tart
directions: In an oven-proof skillet, add sugar, and butter. Melt the butter on medium heat. Add the cream, and stirring constantly, cook until you have a creamy consistency.
Remove the skillet from the heat.
Preheat oven to 225 degrees Celsius.
Arrange the bananas in the bottom of the pan, and fill the gaps with raspberries.
Roll out the puff pastry, and prick it with a fork.
Place the puff pastry over the bananas, and fold the excess dough inwards.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until the dough is flaky.
Unmold, and serve warm with cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: italian duck
directions: Preheat oven at 375 degrees.

Prepare ducks. Filet duck breasts. Slice each filet in half to make 2 thin steaks. Combine flour, onion salt and garlic salt. Dip filets in seasoned flour. Brown in butter in skillet. Place in shallow casserole dish. Saute onion and mushrooms in pan drippings. Add tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix, parmesan cheese and 1/4 cup parsley. Cook covered for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Pour over filets. Combine Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses. Sprinkle over casserole. Top with remaining 1/4 cup parsley. Bake covered until cheese

title: malaysian chicken curry
directions: Sprinkle 1 tsp (5 mL) of the salt and turmeric over chicken; set aside. In food processor, puree together garlic, shallots, ginger and 2 tbsp water to make smooth paste; set aside.
Pressing on side of knife, lightly crush lemongrass. Cut into 2-inch long pieces; set aside.

In large Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high heat. Lightly brown chicken, in batches; set aside. Drain off fat. Reduce heat to medium; cook reserved lemongrass, cardamom, cloves, star anise, cinnamon and mustard seeds, shaking pan, until mustard seeds start to pop, about 1 minute. Stir in garlic mixture, curry paste and sugar; cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 2 minutes.

Stir in stock and coconut milk; bring to simmer. Add chicken and any accumulated juices and remaining salt; reduce heat, cover and simmer until juices run clear when thighs are pierced, about 20 minutes.

Meanwhile, peel and cut each tomato into 8 wedges; remove seeds. Cut eggplants into 2-inch long chunks. Cut long beans into 2-inch long pieces. Add tomatoes, eggplants and beans to pan; bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Uncover and simmer until eggplants are tender, about 7 minutes.

title: elver and ham stuffed eggs
directions: Boil eggs in plenty of cold salted water. Once the water starts to boil, cook for 12 minutes. Cool.
Cover the bottom of a pan with extra virgin olive oil and fry the imitation elver. When done, add a few small pieces of ham. Add cayenne to the oil for a spicier taste.
Open the eggs, remove the yolk, and fill it with the elver and ham. Sprinkle with egg yolk and a little salt.

title: pork in lemon cream sauce
directions: Mix the cream, stock, 2-3 tbsp of lemon juice, lemon zest and mascarpone in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring, and simmer over low heat for about 20 mins. Season to taste.
Cook the pasta in boiling salted water according to package directions.

Heat the oil in a large skillet, and sear the pork for 1 min on each side. Season to taste, then remove the pork from the pan and keep warm. Melt the butter in the pan then add 1-2 tbsp of lemon juice. Add the meat and heat briefly, then add the pasta, arugula, basil and cream sauce. Serve on 4 plates, garnished with lemon wedges.

title: pork schnitzels with waldorf salad
directions: To make the salad, combine celery, apples, nuts and parsley. Toss with mayonnaise and yogurt. Season.
For the pork schnitzels, combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan and sage. Season. Coat pork in flour, shaking off excess. Dip in egg then coat in breadcrumb mixture. Chill for 20 mins.
Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook schnitzels for 3-4 mins per side, until golden and cooked through. Drain on paper towels. Serve with salad.

title: soft milk chocolate and cranberry shortbread
directions: Cut the butter into small cubes, and leave it at room temperature.
Preheat oven to a 150 degrees Celsius. Coarsely chop the milk chocolate with a knife.
Pour the flour, cornstarch, baking powder, and sugar in a bowl.
Add the softened butter, and mix with your fingertips to get a sandy mixture.
Add the chopped chocolate, cranberries, and a little milk, and then bind the dough.
Form a crumbly ball.
Spread the dough into a rectangular 20 x 30 centimeters mold.
Smooth slightly with the palm of your hand.
Bake for about 25 minutes while monitoring that the biscuit doesn't brown too much (otherwise, cover with aluminum foil).
Let the biscuit warm down for about 10-15 minutes, then cut into diamonds or triangles.
Sprinkle with icing sugar.

title: corn souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees
Spray a square baking pan with nonstick spray
In a large bowl, mix together by hand melted butter, sour cream, both cans of corn, and eggs. Add in the corn bread mix.
Pour the batter into the baking dish and bake for 55-60 minutes. Allow to cool

title: chocolate hazelnut brownie
directions: Preheat the oven to 170 degrees Celsius.
Line a 15- by 25-centimeter baking pan with parchment paper.
Cream together the margarine and sugar. Add the chocolate hazelnut spread and mix well.
Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Then add the vanilla.
Separately, sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients just until the flour is absorbed.
Fold in the hazelnuts and dark chocolate.
Bake for 20 minutes being careful not to overbake, as this will cause the brownies to dry out.

title: canadian bacon and eggplant roll-ups
directions: Wash eggplant; pare if desired; cut off stem and blossom end. Cut lengthwise into 10 thin slices. Brush slices lightly with oil and saute a few at a time in a 10-inch frypan until tender. Set aside.

Measure 1 tablespoon of oil into frypan; stir in flour, add milk; cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens. Season with pepper and nutmeg. Combine ricotta cheese and parsley. Lay one slice of bacon on each eggplant slice. Lap on small eggplant slice over a larger slice. Spoon a rounded tablespoon of cheese over eggplant and bacon. Roll around cheese and place seam-side-down in an 11x7-inch baking dish. Pour sauce over eggplant rollups. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a 375 degree F. oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: strawberry cupcakes
directions: Puree 1 cup of frozen strawberries.
Mix whipped topping and pureed strawberries with a spatula until well blended.
Spread generously over the top of the cupcakes and garnish each cupcake with a fresh strawberry.

title: blue berry cheesecake butterfly cupcakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients by hand using a whisk in a very large mixing bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients and beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 30 minutes. 20 Minutes for Cupcakes (which I did)
But just keep an eye on it and test the centers with a toothpick after 30 minutes.
Combine the blueberries, sugar, cornstarch, and water in a pot. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring frequently, until sauce thickens and blueberries begin to break down. Allow to cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla until well combined. Stir in the cooled blueberry mixture and refrigerate until ready to use. (I let mine sit for about 30 minutes in the refrigerate.

title: creamy mushroom soup
directions: Heat the butter in a saucepan, add the onion, mushrooms and celery and saute over a medium-high heat for 3-4 mins, stirring. Pour in the white wine and stock and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 6-8 mins.

Whisk the cornstarch into the cream the pour it into the pan. Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring, until the soup thickens. Season. Divide the soup between 2 soup bowls and garnish with pink peppercorns and parsley. Serve.

title: slow cooker bbq pork
directions: Season pork, if desired, with salt and ground black pepper. Arrange pork in 4-1/2-quart slow cooker sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine remaining ingredients in medium bowl; pour over pork. Cook covered on LOW 8 to 10 hours or HIGH 4 to 6 hours.
Remove pork from sauce. Shred pork with two forks. Return shredded pork to sauce; stir. Serve, if desired, on whole grain rolls.

title: codfish fillet in green coat
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius
Remove the edges from the codfish fillets, place on a baking tray or pan lined with parchment paper.
Mix the almonds and walnuts, add chives and parsley. Add the butter, a squeeze of lemon, and a pinch of salt. Mix to get a thick paste.
Spread over the fillets and bake for about 20 minutes.
Serve with steamed green vegetables.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: To make the dough, sift flour into a bowl then add 1/3 cup sugar, 5 1/2 tbsp butter, egg and a pinch of salt. Meanwhile, dissolve yeast in warm milk then add to flour, mixing until smooth. Cover and let proof for 30-40 mins in a warm place.

Preheat oven to 400°F. In a bowl, mix the cinnamon with remaining sugar. Roll dough out into a 24 x 14 inch rectangle. Melt remaining butter then brush over dough, sprinkle with cinnamon sugar then cut in 1/2 and roll each 1/2 up from the long side to create a roll. Cut into 10 pieces. Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for about 12 mins. Remove from oven, allow to cool on a wire rack then serve.

title: easy, easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough, but you don't need to let it rise.
Use your hands to spread the dough into a rectangle - about 9 x 12 inches.
Spread the dough rectangle with the softened butter.
Sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon over the buttered dough.
Roll up the rectangle from the narrow end.
Using a sharp, serated knife, slice the roll into about 12 slices. Place each slice in a greased cupcake pan hole.
Cover the cupcake pan of rolls with a dish towel and let rise for about 30 minutes.
Bake until light brown in an oven at 350 degrees. Baking time is usually 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with canned or homemade vanilla icing.

title: brunch meatloaf
directions: To hard boil the eggs, place 6 eggs in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring water to a boil over medium heat. Once the water reaches a boil, remove from the heat. Let eggs sit in hot water for 12 minutes, drain then run under cold water. Peel.

Weave bacon in a lattice pattern on a sheet of parchment paper into a 14 x 18 inch rectangle. Combine sausage meat with mustard, remaining egg, breadcrumbs and 4 tbsp water then spread over bacon evenly. Arrange cheese and cucumber over top then lay eggs on bottom quarter along the long side. Roll up, using parchment paper as an aid. Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Remove from oven, cover in foil and allow to rest for 10 mins before serving.

title: "marmita's" gazpacho
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix for 3 minutes or until well blended, check the seasonings and serve with oregano and basil leaves.
Serve cool in a bowl or a cup, add an ice cube if you prefer.

title: hearty ranch salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except Wish-Bone Light(R) Ranch Dressing in large salad bowl. Add Dressing and toss gently.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Preheat a grill pan on high heat. Brush vegetables with oil and cook for 2-4 mins each side, depending on vegetable, until tender. Transfer to a bowl with mushrooms and garlic.
In a separate bowl, whisk together marinade ingredients until well combined. Season to taste. Pour marinade over vegetables. Cover and chill until required.

title: lamb stew
directions: Heat the butter in a large pan and saute the shallots and garlic until softened. Add the lamb and sear all over. Season with salt, pepper, juniper berries and dried rosemary. Pour in the stock, bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer, cover and cook for about 30 mins.

Cook the carrots, potatoes, beans and cabbage in boiling salted water for about 8 mins. Drain and add to the stew for the last 5 mins of the cooking time. Season to taste. Serve garnished with fresh rosemary and mint.

title: homemade corned beef
directions: Cut pockets in the beef and insert garlic slivers and whole cloves.
Place in plastic or glass container and cover with brine made of tenderquick and water.
(Be sure meat is covered with brine.
If necessary, make additional brine in like proportions.
Refrigerate for 10-12 days.
Drain, pick out cloves and garlics, wash with cold water.
Cover with cold water and simmer several hours until tender.
This recipe can also be made with venison.

title: papaya habanero salsa
directions: Blend all of the ingredients in a blender until everything is completely liquefied into a sauce.
Pour the sauce into a pan and heat it up over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Let the sauce cool off and pour it into a container.
Note: The sauce can be stored in the refrigerator for 1 week.

title: braised garlic-ginger chops
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Brown chops about 2-3 minutes on each side; add hoisin sauce, water, soy sauce, ginger, garlic, onion powder and hot pepper sauce to skillet, cover tightly and simmer over medium-low heat for 8 minutes until internal temperature on a thermometer reads 145 degrees Fahrenheit, followed by a 3-minute rest time.

title: bourbon glazed ham with greens
directions: Pat ham dry with paper towls. Melt 1 tbs butter in dutch oven over medium high heat. Cook ham until browned, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer to plate and tent with foil.

Add onion and remaining butter to empty pan and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in garlic, and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Stir in greens and broth and cook covered until just tender and wilted, about 10 minutes. Transfer to plate and tent with foil.

Add sugar, mustard and bourbon to empty pan and cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves and glaze thickens, about 3 minutes. Add ham and cook, turning occasionally, until glazed, about 2 minutes. Slice ham into portions Serve with greens and remaining sauce.

title: spiced lamb salad with basil yogurt
directions: To make the walnut dressing, whisk vinegar with a pinch salt until dissolved. Drizzle in walnut oil slowly, whisking until mixture thickens. Set aside.

Combine salt, pepper and cumin. Lightly coat lamb with oil then roll in spice mixture to coat. Heat a heavy-bottomed frying pan over high heat. Cook lamb for 2-3 mins per side. Let rest, covered loosely with foil, for 5 mins.
Meanwhile, combine beets, watercress and walnuts. Toss with walnut dressing and arrange on serving plates. Slice lamb and arrange over salad. Mix together yogurt and basil. Season. Serve on the side.

title: bitter lettuce salad with cheese & walnut rolls
directions: Bring the sugar to a boil with a little water in a saucepan and stir until it starts to caramelize. Stir in the walnuts and caramelize until they're golden brown. Cool the walnuts on a shallow dish lined with parchment or wax paper.
Mix the cream cheese with the paprika and season to taste. Form the mixture into 8 egg-shaped balls, cover and chill.
For the dressing: puree the jelly, mustard, vinegar and garlic and stir in the oil. Season to taste and stir in the chervil.

Put the walnuts in a plastic bag and finely crush them with a rolling pin. Pour them out onto a shallow dish and roll the cream cheese balls in the nuts until they're covered. Toss the lettuce with the dressing and serve on 4 plates.

title: classic chicken cacciatore
directions: Lightly season chicken with salt and black pepper.

Heat olive oil over in deep 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat and brown chicken, about 8 minutes; drain. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer covered 25 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: blueberry smoothie
directions: Set aside 4 blueberries for garnish. Puree the remainder in a blender with the avocado, hemp protein, coconut water and lime juice.
Place the ice cubes in 4 glasses and pour in the blueberry mixture. Thread a lime slice and a reserved blueberry on a toothpick and use to decorate the glasses.

title: creamy baked pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease a large baking dish.

Heat oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Cook onion for 5 mins, stirring, until soft. Add pancetta and garlic and cook for 2 mins. Add ground beef, increase heat to high and cook for 10 mins, stirring to break up lumps, until browned. Add tomatoes and tomato paste. Season. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 mins.

Meanwhile, cook rigatoni in boiling salted water until al dente. Drain. Toss with butter and 1/2 the Parmesan. Season and set aside to cool. Mix with eggs then transfer to prepared dish along with meat sauce.

To make the cream sauce, melt butter in a saucepan over low heat. Add flour and cook, stirring, for 2 mins. Whisk in milk and bring to boil. Cook for 5 mins, until thickened. Remove from heat, add nutmeg and season to taste. Let cool slightly then whisk in beaten egg. Pour over casserole and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Bake for 30 mins, until golden brown. Let cool for 10 mins then serve.
