Reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add mussels; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until shells open (discard any unopened shells). Remove from heat; set aside, and keep warm.
Prepare grill.

Thread shrimp and fish alternately onto each of 6 (9-inch) skewers. Place kebabs and bread slices on grill rack coated with cooking spray, and grill 6 minutes or until seafood is done and bread is toasted, turning both occasionally.

title: sea bass with papaya salsa
directions: To make the papaya salsa, combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Cover and chill while preparing the fish.
Whisk together 2 tbsp lime juice, fish sauce, sugar and green onions. Set aside.

Preheat grill plate. Make 2 long cuts, about 1/3 inch deep, in thickest part of flesh on each side of fish. Drizzle with 4 tbsp lime juice then stuff with lime quarters and cilantro sprigs. Cook fish over low heat for 8 mins per side, or until cooked to your liking.
Transfer fish to a serving platter and drizzle with lime vinaigrette. Serve with papaya salsa and steamed jasmine rice.

title: pork and fettuccine alfredo casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees F. In a large nonstick skillet stir-fry pork strips in oil until browned, about 4 minutes. Set aside. Cook fettucine according to package directions; drain well; set aside. In a large saucepan melt butter, stir in flour, basil and lemon pepper. Add the milk; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat and stir in pork, vegetables and 1/2 cup cheese, turn mixture into 5-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni-and-cheese bake
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Stir together pasta, cheese, and next 7 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased 11- by 7-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs; bake 10 more minutes or until golden.

title: preserved lemons
directions: Sterilize the jar and cover the base with salt.
Cut 3 lemons into pieces.
Salt the lemon pieces.
Put the lemon pieces in the prepared jar, add salt, pepper and thyme.
Repeat the process until the jar is full of lemons.
If necessary, use your hand to pack the lemons into the jar.
Extract the juice of 2 lemons and add to the jar. Fill the rest with water.
Leave the jar in the pantry and stir it at least once every week for one month.
Can be stored for up to 2 years.

title: vegetable sandwiches with cilantro salsa
directions: For the cilantro salsa, combine all ingredients in a food processor. Process until smooth, adding a little water if necessary.

For the sandwiches, spread bread with butter. Spread 1/2 the salsa on 4 slices. Top with tomato, onion and cucumber. Top with remaining salsa, grated carrot and remaining bread. Cut sandwiches into quarters.

title: mixed vegetables with crispy shallots
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook shallots for 3-4 mins, until softened. Turn up heat and saute for 2-3 mins, until browned and crispy. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Cook carrots in boiling salted water for 8 mins. Add beans and zucchini and cook for 3-4 mins. Drain.
Melt butter in a pan. Add sugar and stir until melted. Add vegetables, vinegar and 2-3 tbsp water. Cook for 2-3 mins, until hot. Serve with crispy shallots.

title: mashed turnip greens
directions: Heat plenty of salted water in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Add the turnip greens. Bring the water back to a boil to quickly blanch the greens.
Drain greens and rinse immediately with cold water to avoid losing color.
Place another large pot over medium heat and add olive oil and garlic.
When garlic begins to release aroma, add greens and saute for a few minutes, stirring occasionally.
Whisk in flour and milk and let it thicken, stirring constantly to prevent it from sticking.
Mash the greens and season to taste with fleur de sel and vinegar.
Serve hot.

title: canadian bacon pizza
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat. Add 1/3 cup chopped green pepper, 1/2 cup chopped onion, garlic and parsley cook, stirring frequently until tender. Add the next 5 ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread sauce over pizza crust, leaving a 1/2-inch border around edges. Combine cheeses; sprinkle half of cheese over pizza sauce.
Combine ground pork and 1/4 cup chopped onion in a skillet; cook over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble. Drain well on paper toweling. Spoon half of pork mixture onto pizza.

Layer Canadian-style bacon, mushrooms slices and green pepper rings on top of pizza. Sprinkle with the remaining ground pork and chopped red pepper. Bake in a 450 degree F. oven for 10 minutes. Top with the remaining shredded cheese and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: pork hock with braised greens
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine water and pork hock. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover, simmer 1-2 hours, or until tender. Remove hock and chill broth until fat can be spooned off surface. Discard fat. Remove meat from hock, trimming any fat.

In 4-quart Dutch oven, cook onion in oil over low heat, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned. Add broth, garlic, vinegar, salt and pepper to onions. Bring to boil, stir in greens and meat from hock, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20-30 minutes. Garnish with chopped green onion and tomatoes.

title: german blood sausage
directions: Dice half of the fat pork and all lean pork in small pieces
Place it in a pan with the chopped onion
Cook over moderate heat until fat begins to render
Lower heat and cook for additional 45 minutes. Add salt, pepper, powdered cloves and ginger. Stir to mix
Grind the fat coarsely.
Stir the fresh pork blood gradually into the meat mixture. Finely dice remaining fat pork and add; stir to mix.
Stuff the mixture into the pork casings and tie it into segments of desired lengths. Cover with water. Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer 25 minutes.

title: potato and meatball salad
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water for 12-15 mins until tender.

Meanwhile, mix the ground beef, onion, breadcrumbs, milk, egg and mustard until well blended. Season. Shape the mixture into small meatballs using wet hands. Heat the oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add the meatballs and fry for 6 mins, turning occasionally.
Blanch the leek in a saucepan of boiling water for 2-3 mins then drain. Drain the potatoes. Gently toss the meatballs, potatoes, leeks, radish and baby corn in a large bowl.
Mix the salad dressing, vinegar, mustard and sugar and season generously. Drizzle the salad with dressing.

title: grilled mexican chicken satay
directions: For Marinade, in small bowl, combine oil, 1 tablespoon cilantro, 1 teaspoon habanero sauce and 1 Knorr(R) Garlic MiniCube; set aside.

On each skewer*, thread chicken, zucchini, pepper and chicken. Evenly rub chicken and vegetables with marinade mixture. In large resealable plastic bag, place skewers. Close bag and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, for Sauce, in medium bowl, combine Skippy(R) Creamy Peanut Butter, water, lime juice, remaining 2 tablespoons cilantro, 1/2 teaspoon habanero sauce and 2 Minicubes.
Remove chicken/vegetable skewers from marinade, discarding marinade. Grill or broil, turning once, 8 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked. Serve with peanut sauce.

title: meatballs with german potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes for 20-25 mins in boiling salted water. Meanwhile, bring the vinegar, duck fat, sugar and stock to a boil. Add 2 onions, pickles and apples and cook for about 2 mins. Drain the potatoes, peel, cool slightly then slice. Pour the onion and apple mixture, with the liquid, over the potatoes and let marinate for 20 mins, turning occasionally.
Mix the ground beef, egg, bread, remaining onion and mustard and season, then form into 8 meatballs. Heat the oil in a pan and sear the meatballs for about 5 mins on each side.
Season the potatoes, sprinkle with chives and capers and serve with the meatballs.

title: sandwich ​​bread
directions: Place the flour, milk, water, butter, honey, salt, and yeast in the bowl of a stand mixer. Attach the dough hook and knead on low speed for 15 minutes. Let the dough rest for about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until it doubles in volume.
Preheat the oven to 210 degrees Celsius or 230 C (depending on your oven).
Press out all of the air bubbles and place the dough in a loaf pan. Let the dough rise for another 30 minutes.
Bake in the preheated oven for about 30 minutes.
Remove the bread from the oven. Unmold the bread and let it cool on a rack before slicing and eating.

title: chicken parmesan meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Mix all ingredients together except olive oil and form into 1.5 ounce balls on wax paper.

In a large oven safe saute pan add oil and heat to medium heat. Add meatballs carefully 1 at a time. Then place in oven for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and serve with additional shredded cheese on top.

title: delicious tres leches cake
directions: Separate the eggs. Beat the yolks with 3/4 cup of sugar until they become creamy and nearly white, approximately 4 minutes. Add 1/3 cup of milk and the vanilla, beat for one more minute.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt little by little while continuing to beat the mixture. Beat well, approximately 2 minutes.
In a separate bowl, beat the whites until they become lighter in color, approximately 3 minutes. Next, add the rest of the cup of sugar and beat for 3 minutes more, until peaks are formed.
Fold the whites into the batter.
Pour the batter into a greased and floured 30 x 15 baking pan and bake for 30 minutes at 180 C or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Remove the cake from the oven and let cool on a rack for 15 minutes.
Prick the surface of the cake with a fork, making deep holes.
Mix the condensed and evaporated milks with 250 ml of the cream in a bowl. Pour it little by little over the cake, allowing the liquid to enter the holes.
For the icing: Blend the rest of the cream with 6 tbsps. of sugar in the blender. When it forms a firm icing, after approximately 3 minutes, spread it over the cake.

title: italian fondue
directions: Pour wine into saucepan and heat over low until simmering. Add garlic, basil, oregano and crushed red pepper, and cook for 2 minutes more.
Mix cornstarch with water, stirring to make paste, and stir into wine. Increase heat to medium and cook until mixture boils and thickens. Reduce heat to low.

Combine cheeses and, using generous handfuls at a time, stir into wine until cheese melts. Repeat, adding cheese and stirring until cheese is gone and mixture becomes smooth, about 3 minutes. Stir in sun-dried tomatoes.
Transfer cheese mixture to fondue pot or crockpot and serve. Keep fondue warm over alcohol burner or in crockpot on lowest setting. Serve with accompaniments.

title: simple summer chicken sandwich
directions: Squeeze lemons to release fresh lemon juice.
Mince or crush garlic in garlic press.
Chop parsley, set aside.

Whisk lemon juice, olive oil, minced garlic, parsley, cracked red pepper flakes, steak seasoning, ketchup & pepper together in bowl, then divide into 2 1-gallon freezer bags. (If freezing, be sure to label bags ahead of time.)
Marinate chicken in bag for at least 30 minutes or longer, or press out air from bag and freeze.

Thaw if frozen. Grill 7-8 minutes per side, basting with additional marinade, if desired. Alternatively, you can pour contents into slow cooker. Cook on low for 3-4 hours or high for 2-3 hours, or place in casserole dish and bake at 400 degrees for 30-40 minutes.
Serve chicken on roll with arugula and tomato basil mayo.

title: cheese fondue with homemade bread
directions: A few hours before preparing the fondue, prepare the bread.
Mix premixed flour and all purpose flour and add 300 ml water.
Knead well.
If the mixture is too dry, add a little more water.
Mix thoroughly for about 5 minutes.
Roll dough into a ball, cover with a cotton cloth and let rise for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 200°C (approximately 400°F).
Divide the dough into three portions.
Roll out portions of dough and sprinkle one with ham, one with black olives and one with nuts.
Shape each piece into a breadstick (long French bread type) and place on a baking tray.
Let rise for at least 30 minutes.
Bake for 20-25 minutes at 200°C (approximately 400°F).
Cool on rack. For the fondue, grate the cheeses.
Rub the fondue pan with cut side of garlic clove and place on stovetop burner.
Add cheeses, except Roquefort, and a few drops of lemon juice.
Heat mixture over medium heat.
Stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, add half of white wine.
Dissolve cornstarch in remaining wine and stir into cheese mixture.
Continue stirring.
Tip: Cornstarch helps the cheese remain creamy and spread evenly on the bread.
When the mixture becomes creamy, add brandy and let the alcohol evaporate.
Season with nutmeg and freshly ground black pepper.
To serve, arrange bread in small pieces on a serving platter and serve frankfurter sausages and apple slices on another serving platter.

title: chocolate brownie
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Line a 15 by 25 centimeter baking dish with aluminum foil.
In a large, microwave-safe bowl add the butter and dark chocolate. On medium power, microwave them together for 30 seconds then stir. Repeat until melted.
Add the sugar and pinch of salt. Mix well.
Then mix in the eggs and the extra egg yolk mixing well after each one.
Sift in the flour and baking powder and stir until just absorbed.
If you choose to use the nuts or dried fruit, at this point you would fold them into the batter.
Pour the batter into the baking dish and bake 20 minutes until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: ensaymada (filipino brioche sweet bread)
directions: Place yeast, water, evaporated milk, sugar, melted butter, egg yolks, and salt in bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with a dough hook attachment. Turn mixer to low.

Once ingredients are mostly combined, begin slowly adding flour. When flour has been incorporated into wet mixture, turn mixer to medium. Allow mixer to knead dough until smooth and elastic, 8-10 minutes.

Collect dough from mixer and shape it into a ball. Dough will be very sticky. Transfer ball to a lightly oiled mixing bowl, cover bowl with plastic wrap, and set it in a warm place. Allow dough to rise until doubled in volume, 2 1/2-3 hours.
When dough has risen, remove it from bowl and turn it onto a well-floured work surface. Cut dough into 16 equal portions.

Using clean hands, roll each dough portion into a 7-inch long log, then use a rolling pin to roll log into a very thin 7x4-inch rectangle. Gently spread rectangle with 3/4 teaspoon of softened butter and roll rectangle lengthwise so it is once again a log (like a cinnamon roll). Shape log into a tight coil and place it in cavity of a 24-cavity miniature tart pan or muffin pan. Repeat with remaining portions of dough. Cover rolls with plastic wrap and allow to rest for 45-60 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350° F.
Remove plastic wrap from rolls. Transfer pan to middle rack of preheated oven.
Bake rolls, rotating pan once halfway through cooking time, until they are golden brown and sound hollow when tapped, 20-25 minutes.
Check to see that rolls are done. Remove from oven or add time as needed. Allow rolls to cool completely while preparing topping.
Use a hand mixer to beat butter on medium speed until smooth. Add powdered sugar and salt, and continue beating until sugar is fully incorporated, 1 minute more.
Spread topping onto fully cooled ensaymada. Top each with a tablespoon of shredded cheese. Serve.

title: homemade doowaps
directions: In a stand mixing bowl, dissolve the fresh yeast in the warm milk. Add the oil, egg yolk, vanilla, flour, sugar, and a pinch of salt. Combine the ingredients using the hook attachment of the mixer.
Lightly oil a bowl and place the dough inside. Cover the dough with plastic wrap and allow it to rest for 2 hours.
Place the chocolate chips in the freezer for 30 minutes.
Once the dough is double its size, take the chocolate chips out of the freezer and carefully mix with the dough, kneading a bit to make sure they are properly mixed in.
Form ball-shaped pieces of 80 to 90 grams each.
Place the pieces on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, letting the dough rest once again for 2 hours to double its size.
Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Coat the dough with the egg yolk and place the baking sheet in the oven. Bake for about 20 minutes.

title: lemon coconut oatmeal waffles
directions: Preheat the KitchenAid(R) Waffle Baker.
Place the melted butter, eggs, brown sugar, yogurt, and lemon zest in a small bowl and whisk to blend.
Finely chop the coconut and set aside.

In a large bowl, whisk together the oats, coconut, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, and nutmeg. Pour the yogurt mixture into the dry ingredients and stir just until combined. Do not over mix. Add more water if needed.
Add in the cranberries; stir.
Cook the waffles according to the manufacturer's directions. Serve hot with butter, powdered sugar, maple syrup, and fresh lemon.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Preheat the oven to 220 degrees Celsius.
In a bowl, mix together the flour, salt, yeast, and water. Knead 15 minutes until smooth and firm. Let rise 1 hour in a warm area.
Once risen, cut the dough in half and roll each half out into a pizza shape.
Top with tomato sauce, ham, bacon, and grated cheese (but really you can top with whatever you like).
Bake for 15-20 minutes depending on how crunchy you like the crust.

title: spanish flag rice
directions: Cook the rice as usual and divide it in half.
Mix 1/2 of the rice with the tomato sauce.
Mix the other half with the saffron.
Make a flag with a stripe of red rice, then a stripe of yellow rice, finishing with a stripe of red rice.
Decorate with the ham after heating it in the microwave for 1 minute (until crunchy).

title: churros
directions: In a saucepan, add the water and cinnamon stick and cook over high heat until the water reduces to 1 cup.
Remove the cinnamon, then add a pinch of salt and the butter. Continue to cook until the butter melts.
Remove from the stove. Add the flour and mix using a wooden spoon until there are no lumps. Let the batter cool for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a large saucepan, heat the oil until it reaches 180 degrees Celsius.
Add the cheese to the batter and mix, then add the egg. Stir until the mix is smooth, which might take a few minutes.
Add the batter into a pastry bag with a star tip.
Once the oil is hot, create the churros directly into the hot oil. Cut into sections with scissors to avoid burns.
Cook until golden brown. Remove and drain the excess oil by placing the churros on top of absorbent paper towels. Once they are cool, cover with a sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: braised lamb shanks
directions: Heat Olive Oil in deep 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat and brown lamb, turning once, about 30 minutes. Remove lamb from skillet and set aside.

Add onions to same skillet and cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until lighty golden. Stir in ginger, garlic, paprika, red pepper flakes and Sauce. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients except potatoes and lamb. Return to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low, then return lamb to skillet. Simmer covered 1 hour.
Season lamb, if desired, with salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes and simmer covered an additional 1 hour or until potatoes and lamb are tender.

title: slow cooker cranberry sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in 4-quart slow cooker. Cover.
Cook 3 hours on HIGH, stirring every hour. Uncover. Stir well.
Cook, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes longer on HIGH or until slightly thickened.

title: creamy cheesy ham tomato sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Bring stock, wine, vinegar, berries, rosemary and shallots to a boil in a 9-10inch oven proof skillet over medium-high heat.
Reduce until there is only about 1/2 cup left in the pan.
Stir in the tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in the cream, salt and pepper, simmer stirring occasionally until thickened 10-12 minutes.
Arrange the slices of ham in the skillet - spreading them out over the skillet - add the chopped pieces of ham as well.
Sprinkle the top with first parmesan and then mozzarella.
Bake in the oven until the ham is heated through and the cheese is melted and bubbly - about 30 minutes.
Serve immediately over fresh cooked pasta.

title: fresh mushrooms and onions
directions: Heat olive oil in a skillet.
Add onion and garlic and saute until the onion is tender.
Add bacon.
Add tomatoes and chile pepper and simmer for 10 minutes over low heat.
Add mushrooms and season with salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook for a few minutes.
Season to taste.
Serve as an appetizer or a side dish.

title: zabaglione with plums
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and marsala in a heatproof bowl. Whisk over a double boiler, until thick and pale. Remove from heat and let cool, whisking occasionally.
Distribute plums and a little reserved juice between serving dishes. Spoon zabaglione over top. Serve with biscotti.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Peel and core the apples. Cut them into quarters, and slice each section, without separating completely. Set aside.
Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius..
Beat the egg, egg yolks, and sugar for about 2 minutes.
Add the margarine and Port wine, and mix on a higher speed for a few seconds.
Add the flour, baking powder, and salt and mix for a few seconds. The dough gets quite thick.
Pour into a round cake pan greased with butter and sprinkled with flour.
Uniformly distribute the apples on top of the dough. Slightly press down the apples, without sinking them into the dough.
Bake for about 30 minutes. Check the cooking with a toothpick, remove, unmold, and let cool.
Once cooled, sprinkle abundantly with powdered sugar.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 180°C (approximately 350°F).
Peel apples and cut into small cubes.
Sprinkle apples with brown sugar and port wine.
Let macerate for 20 minutes.
Beat cheese with sugar until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat egg whites with a pinch of salt until stiff peaks form.
Fold eggs whites into the batter.
Fold apple pieces into batter.
Pour batter into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven for about 40 minutes.
Cake is done when a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Let cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: ceviche
directions: Mix the tuna, lime juice, onion, chile flakes, salt and pepper. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving time. Add the cucumber and carrot to the tuna mixture and mix well.
Spread the tuna mixture on the tostadas and top with slices of avocado to serve. Serve along with ketchup and salsa.

title: antipasto salad wraps
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons of Wish-Bone(R) Red Wine Vinaigrette Dressing and mayonnaise in small bowl ; set aside.
Evenly spread Mayonnaise mixture on tortillas, layer on lettuce and ham mixture. Roll up. Wrap tightly in alumium foil or plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Combine ham, cheese, tomato and 2 tablespoons Dressing in medium bowl

title: baked lentil cheese burgers
directions: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F and spray a baking sheet with the oil.
Combine the lentils, onion, oats, ginger, cilantro, spices, salt, pepper and sugar in a food processor and pulse until chunky. You want a mixture that is moist but not wet.
Let the mixture rest for a few minutes, then shape into patties.
Bake the burgers until they are deeply brown, about 8 - 10 minutes. Then flip and bake for 8 - 10 more minutes.
Serve with melted Jarlsberg cheese, sliced tomato and sprinkles of black sesame seeds on a toasted onion roll.

title: barbecued pork and noodle salad
directions: Place the sesame seeds in large pan over medium heat. Cook, stirring, until browned lightly, then transfer to a small bowl.

Brush the pork fillet with char siu sauce. Heat the oil in same large pan and cook the pork, turning occasionally, until browned all over and just cooked through. Transfer to a warm plate, cover and leave to rest for 5 mins.
Meanwhile, place noodles in a large heatproof bowl. Cover with boiling water and leave to stand for 2 mins. Drain well.
To make the dressing, combine all the ingredients in a screw-top jar and shake well.
Slice the pork thinly and mix gently with the noodles, cabbage, snap peas, carrots, chives and dressing. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and serve.

title: beer bread
directions: In a bowl, pour in the rye or whole wheat flour and the yeast.
Combine the beer with the water and heat until warm.
Pour into the flour.
Mix together, cover, and let ferment for 1 hour.
Mix the all-purpose flour and salt together.
In a stand mixer using the dough attachment (or by hand), start kneading this fermented mixture while adding handfuls of flour.
Stop when the dough becomes soft and elastic.
This process should take about 5 minutes.
Place this dough into a large, greased bowl, cover, and set in a warm place for 1 hour, allowing the dough to double in volume.
Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured work surface and punch down with your knuckles.
Roll it out into a rectangle with about a 30-centimeter width.
Roll up into a sausage shape.
Grease a 35-centimeter round pan and place the dough in it seam-side down.
Sprinkle with flour, cover, and let rest for another 30 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 190 degrees Celsius.
Cut diagonal slits in the top of the dough and bake for 10 minutes.
Lower the heat to 180 degrees Celsius and bake for another 20 minutes.
The bread is done with it sounds hollow when thumped.

title: chapchae (korean stir-fried noodles)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions
In a large pan or wok over medium heat, heat olive oil and 1 Tbsp sesame oil
Add onion slices and garlic and saute for about 1 min
Add rest of vegetables and cook for 4-5 min, until the vegetables are half-cooked and still a bit crispy
Turn heat to low and add cooked noodles, soy sauce, sugar, and the remaining sesame oil
Mix to combine and cook for another 2 min
Add salt or more soy sauce if needed (or if you want it a bit sweeter, add a touch more sugar)
If using sesame seeds, add them at finish

title: blueberry frozen yogurt
directions: In an electric blender or food processor, combine all ingredients.

title: rigatoni carbonara
directions: Place a large pot of water on the stove to boil. When water is rolling, add salt and pasta and cook to al dente, about 8 minutes, reserving 1/4 cup pasta water.

While pasta cooks, heat large skillet over moderate heat. Saute pancetta in a drizzle of oil until it browns, 3 to 5 minutes. Add extra-virgin olive oil, garlic, and crushed pepper flake. Saute garlic 2 minutes. Add wine or stock to the pan and reduce liquid by half, 2 minutes.
Beat together egg yolks, cheese, and while whisking vigorously, stir in a ladle of the boiling pasta water. Beat in parsley and pepper and set aside.

Drain pasta. Add pasta to pan with sauce. Toss pasta with pancetta, then add egg mixture and toss 1 minute, then remove from heat. Continue to toss until sauce is absorbed by and thickly coating the pasta. Adjust seasonings with salt and pepper and serve with extra cheese, for passing.
Read more at: http://www.foodnetwork.com/recipes/rachael-ray/bacon-and-egg-coal-miners-pasta-rigatoni-alla-carbonara-recipe.html

title: spicy mushroom soup with chili
directions: Place the coconut milk, lemongrass and lime leaves in a pot and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer gently for 2-3 mins then remove from the heat and let infuse for 5 mins. Strain the hot liquid and return to the pot. Add nearly all the sliced mushrooms, half the chopped chili and the lime juice. Simmer gently for 3-4 mins. Season to taste with the fish sauce, salt and freshly ground black pepper.
Ladle the soup into warmed bowls and garnish with the rest of the sliced mushrooms and chopped chili and a few cilantro leaves.

title: yogurt-lime sauce
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a small bowl.
Makes a 1/2 cup
Nutritional Information per Serving (2 teaspoons)

title: bruschetta
directions: Cut the tomatoes into slices.
Put slices of bread in a pan and heat in the hot oven for 3 minutes just to brown, without toasting.
Remove the pan from the oven and rub the garlic cloves in the bread. Drizzle olive oil over the bread and top with the sliced tomato. Season with a pinch of salt and top with the mozzarella.
Bake to melt and slightly brown the cheese. Top with chopped basil.
Serve right away with a glass of ginger tea.

title: cardamom panna cotta with apricot sauce
directions: Bring cream, milk, 1/4 cup sugar and cardamom pods to a boil. Simmer for 5 mins. Remove from heat. Stir in gelatin until melted. Strain. Pour into 4 (6 oz) ramekins. Chill for at least 3 hours until set.
Meanwhile, simmer apricots and remaining sugar for 2 mins, until just tender. Let cool. Puree 1/3 of apricots then mix in remainder. Chill.
Unmold panna cotta onto 4 serving plates. Spoon apricot sauce around and sprinkle with pistachios.

title: spicy herbed pork chops
directions: For marinade, in a small bowl combine buttermilk, parsley, cayenne, thyme, salt and pepper. Place chops in a 1-gallon self-sealing plastic bag. Pour marinade over chops, seal bag and marinate in the refrigerator for 6-8 hours or overnight.

Remove pork chops from marinade and discard marinade. Place chops on a kettle-style grill directly over medium-hot coals, close grill hood and grill for 4-6 minutes. Turn chops and grill for 4 minutes more or until internal temperature on a thermometer reads 145 degrees Fahrenheit, followed by a 3-minute rest time.

title: spicy roast chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Season chicken inside and out with salt, black pepper and cayenne. Rub skin with 1 tbsp oil then place in a roasting pan and roast for 30 mins. Arrange onions, zucchini, artichokes, garlic and 2 sprigs rosemary around chicken, season and drizzle with 2 tbsp oil. Roast for another 30 mins. Garnish with remaining rosemary and serve with crusty bread.

title: golden rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan combine the vanilla pudding mix and vanilla soy milk.
Cook and stir constantly until the mixture reaches a full boil.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the cooked rice, raisins, and connamon.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: apple rice pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and flour a 9 1/2 inch springform cake pan. Cream the butter and 3/4 cup sugar with the vanilla extract and a pinch of salt. Mix in the eggs, 1 at a time, then add the rice pudding. Fold in the flour and baking powder. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 40 mins.

Meanwhile, caramelize 1/3 cup sugar in a saucepan. Add the vanilla bean, scrapings and apple slices. Deglaze with lemon juice, cover, and simmer for 5 mins. Add the cornstarch slurry, stirring constantly. Simmer for 1 min, remove from the heat, stir in liqueur gently and set aside to cool.

When the cake is finished, remove from the oven and leave in the pan for 30 mins to cool. Remove the vanilla bean from the apple mix and spread the apples over the cake. Allow cake to cool for 4 hours. Sprinkle with chopped pistachios and serve with whipped cream.

title: spinach, brown bread and eggs
directions: Start to boil the spinach and add the sprig of thyme
Add the oil to a frying pan. Heat at 3/4 max temperature
Chop up the onion and garlic cloves
I used one half of the pan for eggs and one half to fry the onions. Once the eggs are cooked, you can move that part of hte pan off the heat, but keep the heat on the onions.
Add the onions and chopped garlic cloves to the other half of the pan.
Add the eggs to the other half. N.B. cook them over easy, or to your taste

Add the basil and corriander on top of the onion and garlic. 
Begin toasting the bread
From here, wait until the onions are softened, and try to keep your eggs cooking to your likeing.
Taste the spinach to see if it is done. If so, pour out the water and add the spinach and sprig of thyme on top of the onions and garlic and mix.
Once the eggs and bread are done, put the bread on a plate, and put the eggs on top of the bread
Once the spinach is nicely mixed with the onions, and hopefully before all the water is boiled off (some boiled off is good), place the mix on top of your eggs.

title: zucchini bread
directions: HEAT oven to 350°F. Coat a 9x5-inch loaf pan with flour no-stick cooking spray.
BEAT sugar and oil in medium bowl at medium speed of electric mixer. Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, cloves, zucchini and milk. Beat until blended.
ADD eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in nuts. Pour into prepared pan. Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
BAKE about 1 hour or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 20 minutes in pan on rack. Loosen from sides. Remove from pan. Cool completely on rack.

title: lemon garden chicken
directions: MELT Spread in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and cook chicken, stirring frequently, until chicken is thoroughly cooked, about 4 minutes. Remove chicken and set aside.
PREPARE Knorr(R) Rice SidesTM - Chicken flavor in same skillet, according to package directions, stirring in haricots verts and bell pepper during the last 5 minutes of cook time.
STIR in chicken and lemon juice.

title: crunchy lemon chicken
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, warm olive oil. Season chicken with salt and pepper. Place flour, eggs and panko in bowls or plate; dredge chicken in flour, then dip in eggs and coat lightly with panko. Place coated chicken into warm pan and saute, turning, until chicken is done, about five minutes on each side. Remove chicken from pan and set aside, keeping warm.

Prepare couscous by placing olive oil in medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Add shallot and garlic and saute until lightly browned, about 2 minutes. Add couscous and brown for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add chicken stock, bring mixture to a boil, cover and reduce heat to low. Simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

Prepare vinaigrette by combining in small bowl, Dijon mustard, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Slowly whisk in olive oil. Add red onion and Feta cheese. Stir well to combine. Mix vinaigrette with prepared couscous and toss well to combine.
Prepare lemon butter sauce by melting together lemon juice and butter in microwave.
To serve, spoon couscous on plate or serving platter. Top with chicken. Drizzle with lemon butter sauce.

title: apple and vanilla pudding stacks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line two oven trays with parchment paper.
Arrange apples on one tray. Sprinkle with brown sugar and drizzle with lemon juice. Bake 15-20 minutes, until golden and tender.

Meanwhile, using a 2 1/2 inch round cutter, cut 4 circles from each tortilla. Place on tray. Brush with butter and sprinkle with sugar. Bake 4-5 minutes, until crisp and golden. Transfer to a wire rack to cool.
Layer 3 wafers with pudding and apples, finishing with a wafer. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Dust with powdered sugar to serve.

title: aloo paneer in butter sauce
directions: Place potatoes in a medium saucepan. Cover with cold water and bring to a boil. Cook for 10-15 mins, or until tender. Drain then mash until smooth.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a large frying pan. Add onion and 1 tsp salt. Cook for 5 mins, or until golden. Add chili, mustard seeds and garam masala. Cook for 1 min, or until fragrant. Combine with mashed potatoes, paneer, ground almonds and cornstarch. Shape into balls (around 2 tbsp each) and roll in extra cornstarch. Flatten slightly.
Heat oil for shallow-frying in a large heavy-bottomed frying pan over medium heat. Shallow-fry patties for 3 mins per side, or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Combine butter sauce with 1/2 cup water over low heat. Cook for 2-3 mins, or until heated. Add patties and simmer for 2-3 mins. Serve with rice and fresh cilantro.

title: "curry" breakfast soufflé
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit
Add 6 eggs to mixing bowl
Whisk milk into egg mixture
Add cheese & spinach
Whisk mixture and pour into baking dish
Bake for 15-25 minutes
Add salt & pepper to taste

title: chicken marsala
directions: Mix flour, garlic salt and pepper in shallow dish. Coat chicken with flour mixture.

Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in large skillet on medium-high heat. Add half of the chicken; cook 3 minutes per side or until lightly browned. Remove from skillet; keep warm. If needed, add additional 1 tablespoon oil to skillet. Brown remaining chicken.

Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in same skillet. Add mushrooms; cook and stir 3 minutes. Stir in wine, broth and spices. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes or until reduced by half, stirring to loosen browned bits. Spoon sauce over chicken to serve.

title: sunday plum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Crumble Preparation:
Pour all the ingredients in a bowl, and mix with your fingertips for a coarse sand texture. (nuts will emerge but it does not matter).
Set aside.
In a bowl, whisk the butter and brown sugar together.
Add vanilla, cinnamon, and 2 eggs.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour and baking powder and mix for a homogeneous dough.
Pour the dough into a flexible pan or a pan lined with parchment paper.
Cover the surface with pieces of plums, and then add crumble covering the plums.
Bake for about 35 minutes. Insert a toothpick in the middle to verify if it's cooked. The toothpick should come out clean and dry.

title: texas round up ham sandwich
directions: In a small bowl, stir together ham, salsa and rice. Spread ingredients evenly on tortillas; roll up to enclose contents. Cut in half on an angle and serve.

title: vanilla caramel tea cake
directions: For Cake, preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease and flour 10-inch bundt pan; set aside. Microwave milk in microwave-safe cup at HIGH 1-1/2 minutes or until very hot. Add 4 Lipton(R) Vanilla Caramel Truffle Pyramid Tea Bags; cover and brew 5 minutes. Remove Tea Bags and squeeze; cool.

Beat Spread with granulated sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until creamy, about 3 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition and scraping sides occasionally. Alternately beat in flour mixture and tea mixture on low speed just until blended, ending with flour mixture. Pour into prepared pan.

Bake 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes on wire rack; remove from pan and place on wire rack lined with waxed paper. Poke warm cake on all sides with wooden skewer.

Meanwhile, for Glaze, pour boiling water over remaining 4 Lipton(R) Vanilla Caramel Truffle Pyramid Tea Bags in small bowl; cover and brew 5 minutes. Remove Tea Bags and squeeze. Stir in confectioners sugar until smooth. While cake is still warm, brush with glaze until absorbed. Cool cake completely. Serve cake with Tea-Laced Whipped Cream.
Combine flour with baking powder in medium bowl; set aside.

title: recipe for white asparagus frittata
directions: Place the asparagus in a large pan. Add water from a recently boiled kettle to cover them generously. Add some salt. Cook the asparagus for about 7 minutes at a gentle boil. Once the asparagus has had 7 minutes, it should be almost ready. You can check by spearing the thickest part with a sharp knife. If the knife goes in quite easily, with only very little resistance it is ready. Place your slices of ham in the pan, cover it with a tight fitting lid, take it off the heat and set aside for 2 minutes.
Cut the asparagus into pieces of about 2cm / 1/2 in. in length.
In a bowl beat the eggs together with a fork then add the asparagus, ham, parmesan, herbs, salt and pepper and mix through.
Heat the olive oil in a non-stick frying pan on a medium heat and then add the egg mix.
Agitate the mix a little to allow it through to the pan surface so that it cooks. I like to pick up the pan and let the egg mix swirl around and touch the sides to cook.

Push the sides of the frittata down all round the pan, this just loosens it a little making it easier to turn. Cook for about 3 to 4 minutes. The idea is to get it cooked and set as much as possible before turning.

To turn the frittata over, remove your pan from the heat, place a plate on top of your frittata. The plate should be big enough to cover the complete top surface of your frittata. Then in a swift, confident movement, place one hand on the base of the plate and turn the pan upside down, then slide the frittata from the plate back into the pan so that what was the top becomes the bottom.
Put the pan back on the heat and cook for a further 3 to 4 minutes, then serve.

title: pizza pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Cook pasta as directed on package. Drain well.
Meanwhile, break up Italian sausage in large skillet. Cook on medium heat 5 minutes or until cooked through. Drain fat.
Mix sausage, spaghetti sauce, onions, basil, oregano and pepper in 9-inch deep dish pie plate or 2 1/2-quart casserole. Add pasta; mix well. Sprinkle with mozzarella slices.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.

title: pork and beer pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease 4 - 13 oz ramekins.

Heat oil and butter together over high heat. Fry bacon for 3-4 mins, until crisp. Set aside. Toss pork in flour, shaking off excess. Brown for 4-5 mins. Set aside. Saute onions, carrot and garlic for 4-5 mins, until onion is tender. Deglaze with beer. Return pork and bacon to pan along with apple, honey and spices. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15-20 mins, until pork is tender. Let cool for 10 mins then chill.

Spoon chilled mixture between ramekins. Brush puff pastry with egg then cut into 4 squares. Drape over ramekins, egg-side down. Trim edges and pierce tops for steam vents. Bake for 15-20 mins, until puffed and golden. Serve with sauce or chutney.

title: minguichi stew
directions: Place the tomatoes and the serrano pepper in a pot of water and cook them until they become soft.

Remove the vegetables from the pot and place them in a blender. Add a bit of salt and about 1/4 cup of the water used to cook them and blend everything together. Once everything is completely liquefied, set the sauce aside.
Pour the oil into a separate pot and add the onion and the poblano pepper. Cook both ingredients for 3 minutes over low heat.
When the onion becomes transparent, add the sauce and cook everything together until the mixture begins to boil.
Add the cheese and the sour cream and let everything boil a second time.
Turn off the stove and add the tortilla chips on top.

title: herbed millet and tofu casserole
directions: Saute minced onion and garlic in a saucepan sprayed lightly with vegetable oil. Add herbs and then millet. Saute briefly.
Add water and bring to a simmer. Simmer 25 minutes.
Add tofu and spinach and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: clarinha's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 F.
Beat the eggs with the sugar until fluffy. Add the chocolate powder, and the oil stirring constantly. Add the flour and when well beaten, carefully pour a cup of boiling water over the mixture.
Pour the mixture into a baking tray greased with butter and flour or lined with parchment paper. Bake for 30 minutes. If the tray is too large, bake for a shorter time, otherwise the dough will dry.
Remove from oven, and transfer the cake onto a surface lined with parchment paper, let it cool. Cut it in half and place one half on a plate, fill with the jam and put the other half on top.

Prepare the topping: mix everything in a bowl and microwave for 1 minute and 30 seconds. Stir the mixture to check that all the chocolate has melted. Pour the topping over the cake and let it dry. Decorate with strawberries before serving.

title: mexican tortillas, the portuguese style!
directions: In the Thermomix, combine the flour, lard or margarine, and salt and mix for 10 seconds at speed 7.
Add the water and set for another 10 seconds, speed 7.
Then, set at spike speed for 1 minute.

Remove from the Thermomix, wrap the dough in plastic wrap and let it sit for about 30 minutes. Divide the dough into 16 balls of approximately 50 g each. Flour a working surface, place the dough on it and roll out each ball into a large and very thin circle.

Heat a non-sticking frying pan and place the circles on, one at a time, until the tortilla is golden brown on both sides. The process is quick, so do not move away from the stove. Place the tortillas on top of each other to keep them warm.
Growing up, we never wasted food, so we also served these for breakfast with tomato jam - that's a suggestion!

title: apple chocolate crumble bars
directions: Line a baking dish measuring 18 x 18 centimeters with wax paper.
Combine the flour with the sugar, the cocoa, and the Marsala.
Add the butter, chilled and cut into pieces, and work with the tips of your fingers until the mixture resembles oatmeal.
Place 3/4 of the crumble mixture in the baking dish and press well.
Spread the apple jam over the mixture and top with the remaining crumble mixture.
Bake at 180C for approximately 45 minutes.
Remove the crumble from the oven, let it cool completely and cut it into bars.

title: crockpot garlic brown sugar chicken
directions: Place chicken in to Crockpot.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook on Low for 6-8 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Juices can be thickened after cooking by adding a little cornstarch.

title: black-eye pea and barley salad
directions: In a dry saucepan, lightly toast the barley over moderate heat until fragrant, about 5 min., stirring to prevent burning.
Add vegetable broth and bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer gently until the liquid is absorbed and the barley is tender, about 40 min.
Remove from the heat and let stand, partially uncovered, until cooled to room temperature before stirring.
Meanwhile, cook the peas in lightly salted boiling water until just tender but not mushy, about 15 min. Drain, cook, and set aside.
TO MAKE THE VINAIGRETTE - In a small bowl, whisk together the lime (or lemon) juice, zest, garlic, cumin, cilantro, oil, and honey; add sea salt and cayenne pepper to taste.
In a large glass bowl, layer the barley, peas, roasted pepper, tomatoes, scallions and corn.
Drizzle the vinaigrette over the salad and toss before serving. If you like...arrange greens on serving plates and top with the salad.

title: white chocolate mousse
directions: Cut the chocolate into chips.
Melt 60 grams dark chocolate in a double boiler.
When the temperature of the chocolate reaches 50 degrees, remove from double boiler, add remaining chocolate chips.
Mix well until all the chocolate is melted.
Brush melted chocolate on the inside of paper baking cups.
Let freeze and repeat. Brush again, let freeze. Brush a third time, let freeze.
Cool.
In double boiler, melt the white chocolate cut into pieces.
As the chocolate melts, whip the cream with electric beater until firm.
Once the chocolate is melted, add a little whipped cream and mix gently, then add the remaining whipped cream.
Pour the mousse into the chocolate shells (put the rest in classic cups) and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: pumpkin with feta cheese
directions: Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Grease a small cooking tray with butter, add the pumpkin, and season with salt and sugar to taste.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Mix 25 grams of feta cheese, a pinch of oregano, orange juice, yogurt, a pinch of cumin, and a pinch of cinnamon in a medium bowl until you obtain a sauce.
Remove the pumpkin from the oven, pour the sauce on top, add 25 grams of feta cheese, and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove it from the oven, let it cool off, and serve.

title: roasted vegetable and chickpea salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Line a baking pan with parchment paper. Place sweet potato on a microwave-safe plate. Microwave on High (100%) for 4 mins or until sweet potato is almost tender.
Transfer sweet potato to a large bowl. Add zucchini, pepper, tomato, onion, oil and cumin; toss to coat. Season. Place vegetables in a single layer on prepared pan.
Bake for 15 mins or until golden and tender.
Transfer vegetables to a large serving bowl. Add chickpeas, raisins, feta and cilantro; toss gently to combine. Serve.

title: mexican watermelon juice
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a blender and whiz until smooth.

title: beef with baked potatoes and salad
directions: Peal and clean the potatoes
Slice them partially into even slices without cutting all the way, so that they're held together by the base of the potato.
Cut small strips of cheese and place them like a wedge between the potato slices.
Put 2 tbs of olive oil in a oven pan and place the potatoes inside it.
Put strips of butter on top of the potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and paprika for your liking.
Preheat the oven to 220C and place them into the oven for 30 min.
Take the beef steak, the meat must be at room temperature. This is very important. Salt it an pepper it on both sides. Sprinkle some Worcester sauce and a few drops of balsamic vinegar.
Let it set for a few minutes while you pre heat a pan with a tbs of olive oil on medium-high heat.
Place the beef inside the pan, for 5 min, 7 min or 9 min on each side depending on how well you like your meat.
Take the meat out. And let it set for 10 min.
Start prepping the salad. Add the lettuce, seeds, and cabbage. A tbs of olive oil, salt pepper and vinegar for your liking. And mix the ingredients.
By now you should have your potatoes ready to take from the oven.
Place them on a plate, add the salad, cut strips of stake and place them on top.
Have a lovely dinner.

title: humble magnificent cocktail
directions: In cocktail shaker, muddle mint and orange wedges with wooden spoon. Add apple brandy, Pimm's, lemon juice, cinnamon syrup, Demerara syrup, and bitters. Shake well and double-strain into Collins glass. Top with soda water; garnish with mint sprig.

Pinewood Social's Saigon Cinnamon Syrup: In 3-quart saucepan, bring cinnamon, sugar, and water to boiling on medium, whisking. Simmer 15 minutes, then strain through cheesecloth-lined fine-mesh sieve into liquid measuring cup. Cool completely.

title: local chow's sangria
directions: Use half of the lime and orange and save the others for garnish.
Squeeze the citrus juice into your container/pitcher and toss the remains in with it.
Then add the entire peach, strawberries and crystallized ginger.
Add the wine and other liquids and stir.
Let sit for at least 3 hours (overnight is best).

title: grandma inez's pineapple pie
directions: To make the pie, cream sugar, butter, and egg yolks in a medium saucepan with a hand-held electric mixer. Blend in cornstarch and vanilla. Add water and crushed pineapple with its juice; blend once more.
Transfer saucepan to the stove and cook over med heat, stirring constantly until thick. Pour into 9' baked pastry.
To make the meringue, Whip egg whites until they begin to get foamy. Add remaining ingredients and continue to whip until the meringue has reached soft peak stage and is smooth and glossy.
Place meringue over cooled pie. Brown at 400 for just a few min. Store in fridge.

title: blackberry, pear, and ginger cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a 8 inch cake pan and sprinkle with flour. In a bowl, mix the pears and lemon juice.

Beat the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time, adding 1 tbsp flour with the last egg. Sift the remaining flour into the bowl and fold in. Fold in the pears and ginger. Spoon batter into the pan and smooth out. Add the blackberries and press in slightly.
Bake for 50-60 mins, until a skewer comes out clean. Allow to cool in the pan for 5 mins, then turn out on to a wire rack and allow to cool completely. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: blackberry, pear and ginger cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Grease and flour an 8 inch cake pan. Mix pears and lemon juice. Set aside.

Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Mix flour and baking powder then fold in. Add pears and ginger. Transfer to prepared pan and smooth out. Distribute blackberries over top and gently press in. Bake for 50-60 min, until a skewer comes out clean. Allow to cool, remove from pan then dust with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini, lemon and ginger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 320°F.
Grease two baking sheets and line with parchment paper.
In a bowl, beat the butter and sugar until creamy.
Add the salt, lemon zest and ginger.
Add the flour and mix to a thick dough.
Add the zucchini and mix.
Shape cookies or place spoonfuls of the dough on the baking sheets.
Bake until light golden brown.

title: marinated chicken with bean salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.

Arrange chicken in a large baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients then pour over chicken, tossing to coat. Chill for 20 mins. Transfer to oven and bake, basting frequently, for 35-40 mins, until cooked through.
Meanwhile, to make the bean salad, heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Saute peas and tomatoes for 1-2 mins. Remove from heat and toss with remaining ingredients. Season.

title: deep fried anchovies
directions: If you bought whole fresh anchovies, you will need to remove their heads, gut them (if you cut the heads off, the guts come out together with the head) and take out the spine bone.
If you bought fresh anchovy fillets then you are lucky.

Once you gutted the anchovies, put the flour in a large bowl. You will coat the anchovies in flour. You have 2 options: Throw all of them at once in the bowl and using your hands coat them in flour OR coat them one by one (they are quite fragile and this way they will keep their shape better.

Heat up the oil in a medium size sauce pan. When the oil is hot enough, throw in (carefully) the anchovies. Make sure there is enough space in between them. Depending on the size of your pan and the amount you are frying you might need to do it in a few batches.

title: genoan pesto
directions: In a dry skillet, toast the pine nuts 1 to 2 minutes making sure they do not burn.
Add the basil, pine nuts, garlic, cheese, and salt into a food processor. Blend together.
While the machine is still running, stream in the olive oil until everything comes together.
Pesto will keep in the refrigerator a few days.
Serve with pasta, on bread with mozzarella, or mixed into your favorite vegetable soup.

title: bread machine jam
directions: add all items to bread machine
turn on jam cycl
keeps up to 2 months in fridge or freeze

title: italian pasta sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck or hamburger with onion and garlic in large saucepan.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients. Stir to break up tomatoes. Boil gently, uncovered 1 hour. Stir occasionally. Serve over hot cooked pasta.

title: goat cheese salad
directions: Place the cheese in the freezer.
Season the steaks with salt and pepper.
Melt the butter a frying pan, add the steaks, and saute until golden. Before removing from heat, season with ground coriander.
Shred iceberg lettuce and sorrel lettuce leaves.
Add the meat and almonds to the lettuce mix, and season with olive olive, fig spray vinegar, and a pinch of salt.
Remove cheese from freezer, and cut in slices, and add to the salad.
Drizzle a little olive oil on the salad, and grind some pepper on top.

title: homemade ravioli stuffed with chicken
directions: In a large pot, add 2 liters of water, chicken, carrot, onion, garlic cloves, juniper berries, and bay leaf. Add salt to taste, and cook.
Remove only the chicken breast and carrot. Grind in the blender with grated cheese, and about 200 milliliters of the cooking broth.
The remaining chicken and broth may be used for another recipe.
Set aside.
Place the flour on a working surface, and make a hole in the middle.
Put the eggs in the hole, and mix from the inside out, until they are well blended with the flour.
Knead until you get a homogeneous mixture, and smooth dough.
Keep sprinkling with flour the working surface whenever necessary, but not too much, so as not to dry out the dough.
Divide the dough in 3 or 4 portions.
Roll out each portion of dough in long rectangles, as thin as possible.

Place about 1 tablespoon of filling (be generous, because the pasta expands when cooked, and the filling almost disappears) in the center of the dough, at 2 centimeter intervals, depending on the desired size of the ravioli.
Brush with water the ends of the dough with filling, and cover with another piece of dough.
Press with fingers between the filling, and the edges with a knife
Cut into squares, or use a template.
Repeat procedure until all the dough has been used.
Cook the ravioli "al dente" in salted boiling water.
Put the peeled and chopped tomatoes in a saucepan with a bit of olive oil. and the tomato pulp. Bring to a boil, lower heat, and simmer for a few minutes until reduced.
Add about 150 milliliters of the cooking broth, sugar, and salt to taste. Let cook for a few more minutes.
Grind the sauce in a blender, adding more broth if necessary.
Serve the ravioli immediately, topped with the sauce, and garnish with dried parsley.

title: honey-soy chicken wraps
directions: Mix Soy, Honey, Garlic Power, Onion Powder and Pepper in a bowl
Lightly flour chicken thighs and cover with mix
Bake chicken for 25 min at 425
Steam edaname and slice cucumbers/carrots
Assemble wraps

title: cheese and radish salad
directions: Mix the yogurt with a pinch of sugar and season. Fold in half the watercress.
Layer the ingredients into a glass. Top with yogurt mixture and serve.

title: apulian focaccia bread
directions: Knead the flour, the water, and the yeast together in a bowl, cover and let rise for 18 to 24 hours.
In a large bowl, combine the yeast with the starter and half of the water, add some flour and the salt, and begin kneading.

Add the potatoes and the oil, then the remaining flour and water alternating, combine vigorously (until bubbles form in the dough, these bubbles should pop easily) for approximately 10 to 15 minutes. The dough should be very soft. Cover the bowl and let the dough rise for 30 minutes.
Pour some oil in each of two baking sheets and spread it to coat well.
Divide the dough into two parts and knead each part very well. Place the dough in the baking sheet, spread it out completely and let it rise for approximately 2 hours.
Place the tomatoes and the olives all over the dough, sprinkle the dough with salt, oregano, and drizzle with oil. Let the dough rise for 1 hour.
Preheat the oven to 230C.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove the bread from the oven and serve warm.

title: apple, blueberry and pecan bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and line bottom and sides of two 8 x 4 inch loaf pans. Sift flour, baking powder and cinnamon into a large bowl. Stir in sugar, apples and pecans (reserve 2 tbsp of pecans for topping).

Mix butter, eggs, milk and vanilla in a medium bowl. Stir into dry ingredients until combined. Gently stir in blueberries. Pour mixture into loaf pans. Sprinkle with demerara sugar and reserved pecans.
Bake for 30-35 mins, until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 mins. Remove from pans; cool on a wire rack. Serve bread warm or toasted with butter.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 250°C (approximately 480°F).
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape dough into a ball and place in a prepared cake pan or baking sheet.
With a knife, make a shallow cut across surface (or two shallow cuts to form a cross for round bread).
Bake in preheated oven at 210°C (approximately 400°F) for 35-40 minutes.
If baking bread in a pan, remove from pan after 20 minutes and bake for 15-20 additional minutes.
Cool on a rack.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Whisk all ingredients together in a bowl.

title: minute steak sandwiches
directions: In large frying pan, heat 2 tbsp oil over medium heat. Saute onion for 6-8 mins, stirring occasionally, until golden. Set aside.
Increase heat to high. Brush steaks with remaining oil and season. Sear for 1 min per side. Let rest, covered, for 2 mins.
Meanwhile, to make the sauce, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and horseradish. Season.
Fill rolls with arugula, tomato and steaks. Top with onions and sauce. Serve with fries, if desired.

title: bacon twists with bbq ranch sauce
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F.
Layer the bacon on a metal cooling rack set on top of a large cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes, or until about halfway cooked. Remove from oven and let cool slightly. Keep oven on.
Roll out the sheet of puff pastry onto a floured surface a couple times with a rolling pin to smooth it out.
Use a pizza cutter to slice the dough into as many strips as you have strips of bacon.

When the bacon is cool enough to handle, take one strip and fold it in half lengthwise. Fold a strip of dough in half lengthwise. Wrap the dough in a spiral around the folded bacon. Then twist the bacon and secure with toothpicks.

Place the twists on a new baking sheet that has been lightly coated with nonstick spray. Bake the twists at 400 for about 12-15 minutes, or until the puff pastry is golden and the bacon is cooked. Remove and let cool.
To make the sauce, in a small bowl combine ranch, barbecue, and hot sauce. Adjust to taste.
Stir it together and serve it with the bacon twists.

title: orange glazed meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease an 8 x 5 1/2 inch loaf pan.
Mix together all meatloaf ingredients until combined. Season. Press into prepared pan and bake for 30 mins.

Arrange orange slices on top of meatloaf. Whisk together remaining glaze ingredients and spoon over top. Bake for 15 mins. Let rest in pan for 10 mins then slice. Serve cold with salad or hot with vegetables.

title: bonyacalda
directions: In large skillet, melt butter, over medium heat. Add chopped garlic. . Add to garlic and butter the anchovies and sardines. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until garlic, sardines and anchovies are very soft, about 30 minutes. It is imperative that the flavors meld together. It should create a whole new flavor. You should not be able to taste each ingredient separately. Just hints of each.
Smash garlic, sardines and anchovies with a fork. Pour into serving bowl. Serve with bread, celery or cabbage.
This dish is served warm as a dip for hard bread, bread sticks, celery sticks or lettuce leaves.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Steam potatoes in a saucepan of simmering water 15-20 mins, until tender. Toss in 1 tbsp of the olive oil. Sprinkle with sea salt to taste. Set aside and keep warm.

Meanwhile, cut each chicken breast horizontally into 2 thin halves. Flatten each piece between 2 sheets of plastic wrap. Place a slice each of ham and cheese on bottom half of each breast and top with remaining half, pressing down firmly. Coat with seasoned flour, brushing off excess. Dip each stuffed breast in egg, and coat with breadcrumbs.

Heat remaining 3 tbsp oil and butter in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Cook chicken 3 mins each side, until cooked through and golden brown. Place on 4 heated plates. Drizzle with butter from pan, if desired. Serve with steamed potatoes and lemon wedges.

title: swiss inspired onion quiche
directions: Follow package directions for pre-baked crust but only bake for half the time. Your crust will be soft and partially baked, which is the result you want.
Heat the olive oil and butter in a medium-sized skillet.
Add onions and sweat them down without letting them burn.
When they are almost cooked, add vinegar, caraway and/or thyme and salt plus Worcestershire sauce.
Do not overdo the Worcestershire sauce or it will be over-powering.
Continue to cook until soft, tender and sweet.
Taste and add a bit of salt if you want a saltier flavor.
Set aside.
Prepare Cheese And Filling:
Grate cheese and set aside.
Put eggs and milk in blender.
Add pepper and nutmeg.
Blend until foamy and well mixed.
Assemble Quiche:
Spread onions evenly into piecrust.
Top with 3/4 of the cheese.

Add the egg/milk mixture from blender (you may have to whir it up again to re-mix it). The mixture should cover all the cheese and onions. You may end up with some leftover egg mixture depending on the size of your pie pan.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese on and push some of it into the pie. You want some cheese to be showing on top but most should be submerged.
Bake:

Bake at 375° until a knife comes out fairly clean after being stuck into the middle. There is a LOT of cheese and a higher than normal egg to milk ratio in this recipe so it takes less time to bake than most quiches.
Check after 20 minutes and then every 5 minutes after that.

title: wok-fried honeyed chicken
directions: Cut the chicken breasts into pieces.
In a large bowl, mix the garlic, a little chili paste, honey, soy sauce, nuoc mam, and ginger.
Add the chicken and stir to coat with the marinade. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Heat some oil in the wok and add the chicken pieces. Cook until the chicken is tender, stirring almost continuously.
Serve with rice and a salad.

title: cherry "snail" cookies
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk. Mix flour, sugar, egg, butter and a pinch of salt. Add yeast and milk mixture and knead with the dough hook of a mixer to make a smooth dough. Cover and keep in a warm place for about 30 mins until doubled in size.
Meanwhile, bring jam to a boil in a small saucepan, remove from heat and set aside to cool. Add chopped cherries. Set aside.

Preheat oven to 400°F. Line 3 baking trays with parchment paper. Briefly knead dough by hand on a floured work surface, roll out into a 8 x 20 inch rectangle. Spread jam evenly over dough, leaving a margin of about 1/3 inch on each side. Roll up from the long side and cut into 16 slices. Put the "snails" on the prepared pans and press down gently. Let rest for 15 mins. Bake for 10-12 mins. Remove from oven and let cool slightly.
Mix powdered sugar, lemon juice and 1-2 tbsp water. Brush snails while still warm then set aside to dry for 30 mins.

title: oven roasted pork with chorizo ​​and mushrooms
directions: The day before or at least two hours before cooking, marinate the pork shoulder in a baking dish with salt, paprika, lemon juice, minced garlic, coriander, port wine and olive oil. Make sure pork is rubbed and covered with the marinade.
Cook pork in a preheated oven at 180-200°C for 30 minutes.
Remove the pan and baste the meat with the drippings. Return to the oven and cook for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile rinse and dry the mushrooms and slice.
Slice the chorizo.

Remove the pork from the oven and arrange the mushroom and chorizo slices around the pork. Baste with the drippings and return to the oven until the mushrooms are cooked and the chorizo is golden brown.
Serve with white rice and salad.

title: melgaço cookies
directions: Place the flour, the ginger, the yeast, and the salt in a bowl. Mix well.
In another bowl mix the sugar with the molasses, the butter and the egg.
Add the dry ingredients to the liquid ingredients and mix well, until you've obtained a smooth dough.
If necessary add a little water or flour if the dough is too dry or too soft.
Form a ball with the dough, wrap in cling film and chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 180°C Celsius and remove the cold dough from the refrigerator, allow to warm up for 15 minutes.
Roll out the dough on a floured board to a thickness of 2mm. Cut into the desired shape and place in a greased baking tray lined with parchment paper.
Sprinkle the cookies with demerara sugar and bake until cooked (about 8-12 min).

title: peanut butter chocolate cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well, roll into small balls.
Melt together in double boiler. Dip balls in frosting. Place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Refrigerate.

title: caramel apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease a 10 inch springform pan. Caramelize 2/3 cup sugar in a frying pan until golden. Remove from heat and add 1 tbsp butter, until melted. Spread evenly over base of prepared pan and top with chopped apples. Set aside.

Meanwhile, cream remaining butter, remaining sugar, lemon zest and 1 pinch of salt. Whisk in eggs, 1 at a time. Sift flour and baking powder together and mix into batter, alternately with apple schnapps and sour cream. Pour over apples, smooth surface and bake for 30-40 mins. Allow to cool for 15 mins then transfer to a serving plate. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: tortilla soup splendida
directions: In a large soup pot pour in 2 tablespoon of the oil and put over medium heat.
Once the oil is hot stir in the onions and tomatos and cook until the onions just begin to become translucent.
Pour the chicken broth into the pot. Add the chicken breasts. Turn heat up to medium high.
When broth comes to a boil allow the breasts to cook for about 25 minutes, then remove them from the broth. Turn off heat.
Allow chicken breasts to cool. When cool, shred chicken breast meat (discard bone and skin).
This portion of the recipe can be done up to the day before, chicken and broth can be stored in refrigerator until ready to serve.

To make tortilla strips, pour enough oil in a frying pan so that it is at least one inch deep. Heat over high heat. Test the oil by dropping in a small piece of tortilla, when it dances and bubbles, the oil is ready.
Place a small handful of tortilla strips into the oil. Don't crowd the strips, they should have room to move around in the oil. After 1 - 2 minutes turn strips over using tongs.
When stiff and golden brown, remove tortilla strips using tongs and put on a plate covered with paper towels to drain.
Fry the rest of the strips, salt and toss.
When ready to serve, heat the chicken broth to just boiling, add in shredded chicken and heat through.
Add fresh cilantro.
Set up serving station with tortilla strips, cheese, avacado, chopped green onions, favorite salsas and hot sauces.
Invite diners to take a bowl and add ingredients (tortilla strips, cheese, avacado, etc.) to their bowl, then ladle soup over the top and enjoy!

title: paella splendida
directions: Place a medium sized saucepan over medium high heat, rub saffron between your hands and into the pan, use a wooden spoon to stir saffron around in the pan until you can smell its' fragrance. Pour chicken broth into pan and bring to a boil. Once it comes to a boil, turn off heat and allow broth to sit.

Heat a paella pan or large skillet over high heat and place sausages in pan (any casings removed). Chop up sausage with wooden spoon to bite sized pieces and brown. When brown, remove sausage from pan using a slotted spoon, leaving the oil from the sausages in the pan. Put sausages on a large plate or platter and cover to keep warm.
Lie chicken thighs skin side down in remaining fat and allow them to get crispy brown. Using tongs, turn thigh over and allow to cook thoroughly (takes 10 - 15 minutes).
During the last 5 minutes add the sliced chicken breasts and stir in fat until cooked (about 5 minutes).
When cooked, remove chicken pieces from fat and place them on platter with sausages, covered.
Drop sliced pepper and chopped onions and 2/3 of the chopped garlic into remaining fat and stir until just becoming translucent.
Add rice to vegetables and stir, allowing a few grains of rice to brown, about 3 minutes.
Add in chopped tomatoes, peas, capers, pimentos, olives, artichoke hearts, remaining garlic, and paprika and stir to mix.
Arrange the chicken thighs, breasts, sausage, attractively on top of rice and vegetables.
Imbed clams in mixture.
Top with prawns.
Ladle some of the saffron scented broth into the pan, allow to cook, uncovered on medium heat. Continue to ladle in as much broth as possible as the rice absorbs it.

During this final cooking process the rice becomes tender and flavorful, the meat is reheated and the seafood will cook. It is desirable for a caramelized crust to form on the bottom of the rice mixture.
Top with lemon wedges and serve.

title: mixed mushroom and mozzarella pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line an baking sheet with foil. Heat butter and oil in large skillet. Saute onion for 8-10 mins, until soft. Stir in sugar and vinegar. Cook, stirring occasionally, until caramelized (about 10 mins). Season to taste.
Place bread halves on a prepared baking sheet (cut-side up). Spread evenly with caramelized onion and prosciutto slices.

Heat oil in a large skillet on high. Saute mushrooms and garlic for 4-5 mins, until soft. Spoon mushrooms over onions and prosciutto; top with mozzarella. Bake for 5-10 mins, until cheese melts and bread is crisp. Serve topped with arugula.

title: garlic, herb and cheese mushrooms
directions: Preheat broiler to medium. Brush both sides of mushrooms with oil and arrange stem side up on a foil-lined broiler tray. Season to taste.
In a bowl, combine herbs and garlic. Sprinkle evenly over mushrooms.
Broil mushrooms for 4-5 mins, until just softened. Top evenly with cheese. Broil for another 2-3 mins, until cheese is bubbling. Serve with arugula.

title: grilled turkey burger with tzatziki sauce
directions: Combine turkey, parsley, lemon juice, garlic, mushrooms in a bowl. Add a pinch of salt and pepper. Form into 4 patties.
Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium heat and add oil. Cook patties for 5 - 6 minutes per side until they are no longer pink in the middle.
Serve with pitas, lettuce and topped with tzatziki sauce.

title: sandwich bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water and place it in the bread machine. Add the milk, oil, sugar, honey, flour, and salt.
Set the machine to the basic function (approximately 3 hours), light crust.

title: kristie's tortellini alfredo bake
directions:
Melt butter in sauce pan along with cream chz, parm chz, milk, pepper and chopped garlic to taste
add additional milk for desired thickness

Put Cheese tortellini n baking pan with chopped onions, frozen sweet peas and portabella mushrooms
Pour alfredo sauce over the top and bake at 350 for 45 min

title: choco-chestnut financiers
directions: Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.
Melt the butter in a saucepan to a hazelnut color, sieve, and add honey. Set aside.
In a bowl, sift the flour and the icing sugar.
Mix the flour mixture and almond powder.
Add the egg whites.
Stir in butter and crushed chocolate.
Pour in mini financier soft molds.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
To serve, accompany with a ball of vanilla ice cream.

title: stromboli roll
directions: Defrost dough in refrigerator according to package directions. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Roll dough into a 10x15 inch rectangle.

Beat egg with grated cheese and brush over dough. Layer with meats and cheese to taste, and sprinkle with basil. Roll tightly lengthwise; seal edges. Place sealed side down on lightly greased cookie sheet, sprinkle with paprika, and bake for 13 to 15 minutes. Slice and serve hot or cold.

title: "wonderland" excessively crunchy peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees.

Toast the peanuts on a baking sheet in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 10 to 12 minutes. Cool the peanuts to room temperature before chopping by hand with a cook's knife into 1/4-inch pieces. Set aside.
In a sifter combine the flour, baking powder, and salt. Sift onto a large piece of wax paper and set aside until needed.

Place the light brown sugar, peanut butter, unsalted butter, and the corn syrup in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle. Beat on medium for 4 minutes. Use a rubber spatula to scrape down the sides of the bowl, then beat on medium for 2 more minutes. Scrape down the bowl. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating on medium for 1 minute and scraping down the sides of the bowl after each addition. Add the vanilla extract and beat on medium for 1 minute. Operate the mixer on low while gradually adding the sifted dry ingredients until incorporated, about 1 minute. Add 3/4 cup shopped peanuts (the remaining peanuts are for the topping) and beat on medium for 10 seconds. Remove the bowl from the mixer and use a rubber spatula to finish mixing the i

Transfer the batter to a 9x13x2-inch nonstick baking pan. Use a rubber spatula to spread the batter in an even layer. Place the pan on the center rack of the preheated oven and bake for 35 minutes until a toothpick inserted in the center of the brownie comes out clean. Remove from the oven and allow to stand at room temperature for 1 hour before finishing with the topping.
Heat the heavy cream in a 1-1/2 quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Bring to a boil.
Place the chopped semisweet chocolate in a 3-quart bowl. Pour the boiling cream over the chocolate and stir with a whisk until smooth. Congratulations... you have just created ganache!
Pour the ganache over the cooled brownie. Use a cake spatula to spread the ganache evenly over the entire surface of the brownie.
Combine in a 3-quart bowl the chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, and the remaining 3/4 cup chopped unsalted peanuts.
Sprinkle the chips and nuts evenly over the ganche. Refrigerate the brownie for 1 hour before cutting. This will make the ganche layer firm enough to cut.

Use a serrated knife with rounded tip to cut the brownie into 24-2-inch squares. For a clean cut, heat the blade of the knife under hot running water and wipe the blade dry before making each cut. Serve immediately or store the brownies in a tightly sealed container.

title: mexican curry
directions: In 12 inch skillet, brown soy burgers or meat and onion, then drain.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Add spices, mix well and bring to a boil.
Add rice, stir and cover.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the water is absorbed, about 30 minutes.
To serve, cover the bottom of a plate with corn chips.
Scoop about 1/2 cup of the curry on top.
Add toppings such as cheese and lettuce to taste.

title: party antipasto salad
directions: Combine all ingredients before adding the vinaigrette.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: hot chocolate-2
directions: Combine the milk and water and sugar in a medium saucepan.Heat mixture over medium heat until it reaches a rolling boil.
Add the chocolate chips and cocoa powder.
Whisk into milk mixture and return to boiling boil.
Mixture will thicken.
Reduce heat to very low.
Blend using immersion blender until thick and foamy.
If the cup of chocolate is too bitter/sweet/ strong stri in some cream or add in more milk.

title: chedd'r bac'n scalloped potatoes (good luck potatoes)
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Slice potatoes into thin slices. Arrange in casserole dish. Sprinkly lightly with 1-2 teaspoons of salt, and add water. Cover with Let Thy Food Chedd'r Bac'n Dip, and spread evenly.
Cover and bake 70-90 minutes or until potatoes are tender. .
Enjoy!

title: sweet `n sour chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to boil.
Cut wings at joints, discard tips.
Place wings on greased rack of broiler pan, brush generously with sweet and sour sauce.
Broil 8-10 minutes on each side.
Brush with remaining sauce.
