directions: Heat oil in a deep frying pan, add the chicken, and cook over a medium heat for 4-6 mins, turning once. Add the almonds and cook, turning, for 1 minute. Reduce the heat and add the onion and garlic, cook for 1-2 mins.
Add the tomatoes, white wine, and 2/3 cup water. Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper and simmer for 6-8 mins.
Stir through the olives and parsley. Serve with crusty bread.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir the soup, milk, soy sauce, black pepper, beans and 2/3 cup onions in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350°F. for 25 minutes or until the bean mixture is hot and bubbling. Stir the bean mixture. Sprinkle with the remaining onions.
Bake for 5 minutes or until the onions are golden brown.

title: tzatziki sauce
directions: Peel your cucumber and slice it open. Using a spoon, discard the seeds (nobody wants seedy tzatziki). Then shred the cucumber with a cheese grater. After you have 1/2 cup, put it in a bowl with the kosher salt and let it hang out while you prepare the rest of the recipe.
Mix the yogurt, sour cream, lemon juice, rice vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl. Then add the garlic, fresh dill and Greek seasoning.
Take your cucumber and squeeze it through some paper towels over the sink to get rid of any excess water. Then add the cucumber to the yogurt mixture. Mix it all together and taste it.

After tasting it add salt and pepper as you like. Then put the dip in the refrigerator to meld. I'd recommend letting it sit in the in the fridge for at least a couple of hours so the flavors all come together.
Serve with pita, mixed veggies, chips/crackers or as a side to gyros!

title: banana caramel cake
directions: STEP ONE
STEP TWO
STEP THREE
*Percent Daily Values are based on a 2,000 calorie diet.

title: vegan fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 325 degrees. Boil first 8 ingredients together for 3 minutes. Allow to cool. Sift cake flour before measuring; re-sift with baking powder and soda. Stir flour mixture gradually into other mixture. Add chopped nuts and fruit. Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar or ice with a citrus glaze.
Mix above ingredients until smooth. Drizzle over cake.

title: pineapple banana layer cake
directions: Bake in greased and floured pans at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. (Test with toothpick.)
Cook over high heat; boil until it spins a thread.
Slowly pour syrup onto beaten egg whites, while beating with electric mixer.
Place cake layer on plate. Add pineapple and bananas. Cover with icing. Repeat until all layers are covered. Then spread icing all over cake.

For Coconut Cake: Omit pineapple and bananas and use 2 coconuts; melt 1/4 cup butter in double boiler. Add 1 cup sugar. Stir in 3 beaten eggs, juice of 1 1/2 lemons and grated rind of 1 lemon. Cook, stirring until thick (20 to 30 minutes). Chill. Place cake layer on plate. Add filling. Sprinkle with coconut. Cover with icing. Repeat until all layers are covered. Then spread icing all over cake and sprinkle outside with coconut.

title: kfc coleslaw
directions: Slice cabbage paper thin, and toss lightly with sugar, shredded carrots.

Sprinkle with salt and pepper and drench it all with milk. Cover and refrigerate for about 15 minutes. Meanwhile, combine mayonnaise (not salad dressing), buttermilk, celery seed, Tabasco and minced onion.
Mix well with cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate again at least an hour before serving.

title: toasted onion and garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Toss potatoes with oil in large bowl. Sprinkle with Seasoning; toss again to coat well.
Arrange potatoes in single layer on foil-lined 15x10x1-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: ginger mint smoothie
directions: Throw everything into a blender and swirl until desired consistency is reached.
I like mine really smooth and creamy.

title: potato and leek soup
directions: Heat the butter in a saucepan, add the onions and garlic and saute for 2-3 mins. Add the leeks and potatoes (set some aside to fry, for garnish) and saute for 1-2 mins. Pour in the stock and milk. Bring to a boil then cover and simmer for 12-15 mins, until tender.
Meanwhile, heat the oil in a frying pan, add the reserved potato cubes and fry for 8-10 mins, until golden and cooked through.
Remove the soup from the heat and blend in a food processor. Season and stir in the cream. Divide the soup between 4 bowls and top with the fried potato and a little leek. Serve.

title: pineapple chicken casserole
directions: Spray 9x13 oven dish with Pam. Mix together in a bowl the soups bell pepper onion rice and pour into baking dish , lay out your chicken pieces on top,our melted butter over chicken then top with the can of pineapple. DO NOT STIR. BSKE IN. 350 Degree oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Depending on the size of your chicken pieces.
tags: cream of chicken soup each of

title: italian grilled tuna
directions: Combine the tuna steaks and lemon juice and marinate for 15 minutes. Prepare an outside grill with an oiled rack set 6 inches above the heat source. On a gas grill, set the heat to medium.

Grill or broil the tuna 6 inches from the heat source for 4 to 5 minutes on each side. Combine all remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour the sauce over the tuna steaks to serve.

title: spicy ribs with fruit salsa
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Mix the honey, ketchup and sambal oelek together and season. Coat the ribs with sauce. Place the ribs on a baking sheet covered in foil and bake for 35-40 mins, turning half way through.

Heat the oil in a pan, add the onion, garlic and almonds and saute for 3-4 mins. Add the pineapple, oregano, cloves, thyme, cayenne pepper and cinnamon and season. Mix in the tomatoes and juice from the pineapple. Simmer for 8-10 mins. Fold in the bananas, lemon juice and sugar and season. Divide the ribs and sauce between 4 plates and serve.

title: pineapple mushroom chicken shish-kebabs
directions: Mix all marinade ingredients together.
Simmer 5 minutes; cool.
Remove skin from chicken and cut meat into 1 1/2 inch chunks.
(Boneless breasts can be used.)
Marinate chicken in sauce mixture for 1 hour.
Alternate chicken, pineapple, mushrooms, and green peppers on skewers.
Grill for 20 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Mix oatmeal, baking soda and flour.
Add to sugar; mix well.
Form into walnut-sized balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Butter bottom of glass, dip in sugar and mash balls flat.
(Redip in sugar as needed.)
Bake in 350-degree oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet then remove with spatula.
Cool.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together without leaving lumps, if you have some lumps you may use an immersion blender.

Take a small, nonstick skillet and brush it with butter. Pour a small ladle of the batter into the pan set over medium heat, when the surface starts bubbling, turn and cook the pancake on the other side.
Top with your choice of toppings.

title: homestyle sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground beef with the onion and green pepper over medium-high heat for 7 to 9 minutes; drain off the excess liquid.
Add the remaining ingredients except the buns; mix well.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over the hamburger buns.

title: potato sloppy joes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Grease a baking sheet. Place potato wedges on baking sheet and spray with oil. Bake 25 mins or until golden and crisp.

Meanwhile, for the Sloppy Joe mixture, heat vegetable oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Add onion and pepper and cook, stirring, 2-3 mins or until tender. Add pork and cook, stirring, with a wooden spoon to break up clumps, for 5 mins or until browned. Stir in peas, tomato sauce, mustard and vinegar. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 6-8 mins or until thick.
Spoon Sloppy Joe mixture onto potatoes and sprinkle with cheese and green onion. Serve with salad.

title: oven baked chicken with pineapple juice
directions: Preheat Oven 350 degrees:
Place the chicken thighs in a baking pan.
In a small bowl combine the pineapple juice, lemon juice, drizzle of olive oil and the salt, pepper, ground oregano, ground cumin and mix. Drizzle this over the chicken.
Sprinkle the crushed croutons over the chicken and grate the Romano cheese over the chicken.
Place in the oven and bake 45-50 minutes or until the juices run clear.

title: muscato chocolate creamcheese dip
directions:
Melt baking chocolate in sauce pan over low/medium heat with Muscato wine
Continue stirring until chocolate is melted
Once chocolate is melted add half and half and stir
Add basil leaves (crushed not chopped) and stir
Add cream cheese and stir

If mixture is too thick add more wine until mixture thins out
Turn heat to low
Add sugar and taste to reach desired sweetness
Let simmer for 5-10 minutes stirring occasionally until desired consistency is reached
Dip fruit or serve separately for dipping

title: slow cooker teriyaki pork roast
directions: visit http://www.sixsistersstuff.com/2015/07/slow-cooker-teriyaki-pork-roast.html for the rest of this recipe and more delicious recipes

title: ham and sweet potato frittata
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 6 x 10 inch loaf pan. Line base and sides with parchment paper.
Place sweet potatoes on a baking sheet; drizzle with half the oil. Bake 10-15 mins, turning once, until tender.
Meanwhile, heat remaining oil in a large frying pan on high. Saute onion and garlic 3-4 mins, until tender; allow to cool.
In a large bowl, whisk together eggs and cream, until combined. Stir in ham, peas, pepper, chives and cooked onion and garlic. Season to taste.
Pour mixture into pan, layering with sweet potato. Bake 30-35 mins. Cool slightly; cut into slices. Serve with arugula salad.

title: chicken salad bar
directions: Preheat the grill to medium-high. Combine chicken, oil, Worcestershire sauce and garlic in a bowl. Grill chicken 5-6 mins each side. Slice and keep warm.
For the blue cheese dressing, combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Arrange all ingredients on platters. Serve with dressings.

title: honey mustard chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Arrange bread in single layer on a baking sheet. Drizzle with 1 tbsp oil and season. Bake for 6-8 mins, until crisp and golden.
Meanwhile, heat grill pan over medium heat. Brush chicken with 1 tbsp oil and season to taste. Cook for 5-6 mins per side, until cooked through. Let rest for 5 mins. Slice thinly.
Combine avocado, celery and onion. Whisk remaining ingredients together. Season then toss with salad. Serve topped with chicken and croutons.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, and egg with 1 stalk celery, sliced grapes, 1 small onion, 1 tsp celery seed, 1 tsp salt.
In a separate bowl, add the grated onion, mayonnaise, horseradish, lemon juice mix well.
Add pecans and mix well.refrigerate overnight.

title: glazed ham
directions: Place over ham a 16 ounce can of pineapple rings with juice.
Put maraschino cherries in the center and stick a few cloves around the ham.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for around 3 hours.
Makes a terrific gravy.

title: lemon crab tea time sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients except bread; set aside.
Trim crusts from bread; cut bread into circles, rectangles, squares or triangles. Spread crabmeat mixture on bread and garnish, if desired, with additional grated lemon peel.

title: walnut cake
directions: Take the Sultanas OR Raisins and soak them in the half a cup of Apple juice
Grease and line a loaf tin
Preheat the oven to 180 degrees , fan assisted
Sift the flour into a large mixing bowl
Mix all dry ingredients together in the mixing bowl
Peel and grate 1 large Apple OR 2 small apples into the mixing bowl
Put the milk and butter together in a pan and heat through until the butter has melted , stir together.
Place sultanas/raisins into the bowl , do not drain the excess liquid away
Add in a beaten egg
Add in the milk and butter liquid
Stir all ingredients and mix well
Put the cake mixture into the loaf tin and place in oven for approx 35 mins

title: ice cream cake
directions: Sprinkle a 10 inch springform pan with semolina.
Whip cream to stiff peaks. Fold in raisins, crumbled meringue, 7 oz chopped chocolate, almonds and walnuts. Transfer to prepared pan, smooth surface, cover and freeze for at least 24 hours.
Around 30 mins before serving, remove ice cream from freezer. Let sit at room temperature to thaw slightly.

Meanwhile, toast sliced almonds in a dry frying pan until golden brown. Let cool. Melt remaining chocolate then let cool slightly. Transfer cake to a serving plate and arrange small meringues on top. Drizzle melted chocolate over top and sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: gluten free beetroot sandwich bread
directions: Preheat oven at 350 degree Fahrenheit and prepare a cookie sheet with a liner. Also prepare a baking 9*5 inch loaf pan by greasing it properly.
Place the chopped beets pour 1 tbsp. honey over each piece of the beets and bake for 10 minutes.
Take the beets out of the oven, let it cool for couple of minutes and grind as fine as possible.
In a mixing bowl combine eggs, flax oil and rest of the honey.
In another mixing bowl combine almond flour, baking soda and salt.
Add the beets to the almond flour and mix well with a spoon until well coated.
Lastly, add the wet ingredients into the almond flour and mix until all the wet and dry ingredients blend well.
Lastly, add the wet ingredients into the almond flour and mix until all the wet and dry ingredients blend well.
When done take it out of the oven and let it cool very well and cut into desired slices.
Serve at room temperature or toasted or as a sandwich.

title: miniature fruit tarts
directions: Some pastry shells may bake into uneven shapes. If this happens, split the shells so the top half is even all the way around. Then, trim the bottom half so the sides are even. When you assemble the tart, it will stand upright --
On a lightly floured surface roll pastry slightly to flatten creases. Cut puff pastry circles and diamonds using 2-inch cutters. Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush pastry rounds with egg white. Stir together pecans and the 1 tablespoon sugar. Sprinkle pecan mixture over pastry shapes. Or, use the pearl sugar instead of nut mixture.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for 12 to 14 minutes or until puffed and golden. Transfer pastries to a wire rack. Cool.

Meanwhile, in a small saucepan mix orange juice, corn syrup, and cornstarch. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Transfer to a small bowl; cover and cool to room temperature.
In a small mixing bowl stir together yogurt and pudding.

Split pastry rounds horizontally. Spread about 1 teaspoon of the yogurt mixture on the bottom half of each round. Arrange fresh fruit atop pudding. Brush the fruit with orange juice mixture. Replace tops. Cover and chill for 1 to 24 hours.
To tote, arrange the tarts in single layers in shallow covered plastic containers or baking pans. Cover the pans with foil. Stack the pans in a cooler. Makes about 45.

title: holy grass mousse pie
directions: Grind in a blender the oat and the brown sugar. Put in a bowl and add the unsalted butter, mixed using your hands. Put into a pie baking pan and bake for 30 minutes in 400F or 200° temperature;
Grind in a blender the table cream and the holy grass. Sift then. Reserve this cream.;
Grind in a blender the condensed milk for 1 minute, then put together the cream and for the last the lemon juice;
Take the pie crust, put it on a dish plate and put the cream inside. Take the refrigerator at least 2 hours. Serve it!

title: banana avocado smoothie
directions: put your frozen banana into the blender them empty your avocado too
then blend

the last step and it is optional 
-wet your glass 
-then put it in sugar
AND VOUALA

title: baked or grilled fish with dijon glaze
directions: Preheat oven or grill to 500 degrees (or 450 degrees if that temperature is just too scary at first). Heat the pan on high heat, until it is very hot.
While it is heating, brush glaze over all surfaces of the fish, particularly all flesh.
To Bake: When the pan is hot (using potholders) put the fish in and brown on one side. Turn the fish after 2 minutes and put the pan into the oven.
Bake for another few minutes. Remember: 5 minutes to the inch of thickness.

To Grill: Put fish on grill and cook, turning only once (for 5 minutes per inch). Take the fish out of the oven or off the grill, and immediately transfer it to a warmed serving dish or warmed individual plates.Add wine to the pan and cook at medium high, whisking constantly until the sauce is reduced by half. For grilling, cook wine and 1 tbsp. Dijon glaze in a small pan. Pour over the fish, garnish with fresh herb, and serv

title: blueberry tarts
directions: Pastry Preparation:
In a bowl, mix flour and butter by hand.
Add egg yolk, sugar, and almond meal. Mix until well blended.
Roll out dough on parchment paper, place between 2 baking trays. Refrigerate for at least one hour.
Almond Cream Preparation:
Cream butter and sugar, add cornstarch, almond meal, and finally, egg and egg yolk. Mix until well blended.
Preheat oven to 356F.
Cover 6 tart pans with dough. Fill to 2/3 full with almond cream. Bake for 13 minutes.
Cool and unmold.
Heat jam and pour in frozen blueberries. Mix gently.
Divide fruit between tart pastry, and set aside for about 30 minutes before serving, just until blueberries thaw.

title: coconut lime bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease a KitchenAid(R) Professional-Grade Nonstick 9" x 9" Square Pan (or 8x8 square pan) with baking spray, line with parchment paper and grease parchment with baking spray.

In the bowl of a KitchenAid(R) Pro Line(R) Series 16-Cup Food Processor, combine all the ingredients for the crust, except the butter. Pulse until well combined. Add the butter pieces and pulse until crust starts to come together (will look like wet sand).
Turn dough out into the prepared pan. Using your fingers, press evenly into the bottom of the pan.
Bake crust for 10 minutes or until slightly brown around the edges. Remove from oven until filling is ready.

While crust is baking, prepare the filling. In a large bowl, whisk together the eggs and granulated sugar until thickened, about 2-3 minutes. Whisk in the rest of the ingredients for the filling and mix until combined and thickened.
Pour the filling into the warm baked crust and bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool completely to room temperature on a wire rack.
Chill bars for at least 2 hours or overnight before cutting.
To serve, use a sharp knife to cut into about 9 bars. Whip the heavy cream, coconut extract and powdered sugar until soft peaks form. Top each bar with coconut whipped cream and fresh lime zest.
Store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: spicy pork loin sandwich with chile aioli
directions: 1. In food processor, add egg yolks, vinegar, salt, pepper, garlic, sugar, paprika, and hot pepper sauce. Process 30 seconds. Leaving processor on, very slowly add oils in a thin stream to create an emulsion. Refrigerate
1. Rub pork with spice blend. Roast or saute 20 to 30 minutes, until internal temperature reaches 145 degrees F. Hold warm 10 minutes.

2. Cut into very thin slices. Generously spread cut sides of rolls with Chili Aioli. Divide pork among rolls. Top with salsa such as a green tomato and cucumber salsa or lettuce leaves and tomato slices

title: rice cakes with aioli
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water for 10-12 mins. Drain and rinse under cold water.

Meanwhile, in a frying pan, heat 2 tsp oil over high heat. Saute onion and garlic for 1-2 mins, until onion is tender. Add prosciutto and cook until crisp. Transfer to a large bowl. Add cooked rice, Parmesan, eggs, pine nuts, sun-dried tomatoes and parsley. Season.

Heat remaining oil in large frying pan over high heat. Working in batches, spoon 1/4-cupfuls of rice mixture into pan. Using a spatula, flatten slightly and shape into rounds. Cook for 2-3 mins per side, until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Keep warm.
To make the aioli, combine mayonnaise, garlic and lemon zest. Serve with rice cakes and arugula salad.

title: lemon herb tilapia casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Toss potatoes and onions with 1/2 cup of the Seafood Sauce. Spread evenly in greased 13x9-inch baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender. Meanwhile, brush remaining 1/4 cup Seafood Sauce over fish and tomatoes. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Arrange fish and tomatoes over potatoes. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork and potatoes are tender. Garnish with olives, if desired.

title: tys sweet chops
directions: In a bowl, combine rum, green onions, dates, steak sauce, molasses, parsley, garlic, lemon pepper, onion powder and salt. Pour into a 13x9x2-inch baking dish. Brush chops lightly with a little oil and brown 2 minutes on each side in a hot skillet; arrange browned chops on top of date mixture. Bake, uncovered, in 350 degrees oven for 25-30 minutes, until internal temperature on a thermometer reads 160 degrees F.

title: chicken with peppers & goat cheese
directions: Season chicken, if desired, with salt and ground black pepper. Dip chicken in flour, coating well; shake off excess. Heat 1 tablespoon Olive Oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and cook chicken, turning once, 5 minutes or until thoroughly cooked. Remove chicken and keep warm.

Heat remaining 1 tablespoon Olive Oil in same skillet over medium heat and cook bell peppers, stirring frequently, 4 minutes or until crisp-tender. Add shallots and cook 2 minutes. Add garlic and cook, stirring frequently, 1 minute. Stir in Sauce and simmer 5 minutes or until slightly reduced.
To serve, spoon sauce over chicken and sprinkle with goat cheese.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Grease a 10-inch springform pan and line the edge with aluminum foil. Cook the pasta in boiling salted water according to the package instructions. Drain.

Meanwhile, heat the oil in a skillet and saute the beef until browned and crumbly. Add the bacon and cook for 1 min. Add the onion, garlic, carrots and rosemary and saute for 2 mins. Add the tomato paste and stir in. Add the tomatoes and simmer over a low heat for 20 mins, stirring occasionally. Season with salt, black pepper and a pinch of sugar. Remove from the heat and mix with the pasta.

In a bowl, beat the eggs and 3/4 of the pecorino. Season with salt and a pinch of nutmeg. Stir into the pasta mixture. Spoon into the prepared pan and sprinkle with the remaining pecorino. Bake for 25-30 mins, until golden and bubbling. Allow to cool a little, then carefully remove from the pan and garnish with the reserved rosemary.

title: jamaican curried goat
directions: Wash & cut meat into bite-sized pieces. Leave in the bones as they add flavor & become chewable after cooking. Combine seasoning ingredients & rub into meat. Cover and marinate 1 1/2 hours or overnight. Boil water in heavy saucepan or Dutch oven. Add goat meat & seasonings & marinade, stir.

Cover pot & cook slowly over medium heat, stir occasionally. Continue to simmer for at least 1-2 hours or until meat is tender and easily separated from bones. Add more water if necessary. Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit salad with lime
directions: Stir 1 cup water, lime juice, sugar and lime zest over low heat for 2-3 mins, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10-12 mins, until thickened slightly. Add liqueur. Let cool.
Combine fruit and mint in a large bowl. Toss with syrup around 15 mins before serving.

title: pumpkin cream with blue cheese, camembert skewer with gin
directions: Peel pumpkin pieces, potato and chop.
Chop leek.
Cook in boiling water for about 25 minutes.
When vegetables are done, set aside some broth.
Drain vegetables.
Add blue cheese to vegetables and drizzle with olive oil.
Puree with an immersion blender and add some broth, if needed.
Season with salt.
Dust camembert cheeses with flour, dip in egg and coat with breadcrumbs and fry in plenty of hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Thread fried cheese onto a skewer and top with a little gin tonic jelly on top.
Serve with pumpkin cream.

title: easy spinach dolmades
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic and saute for 2-3 mins until tender. Add the ground lamb and spices and cook for 4-5 mins, breaking up lumps with a spoon. Stir in the rice. Set aside to cool.

Stir in the lemon juice and herbs. Season to taste. Shape level tablespoonfuls of the mixture into log shapes, pressing together firmly. Place a log near the bottom of a spinach leaf. Fold over sides then roll up tightly. Repeat with remaining ingredients. Serve with lemon wedges, yogurt and pita bread.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Simmer on low until the rice is cooked.
You may eventually want to add about another cup or so of water, if the soup gets too thick.

title: spanish pork casserole
directions: Place beans, undrained tomatoes, rice and seasoning packet, onion, bell pepper, olives, water, garlic and pepper in 5-quart slow cooker. Mix until well combined. Place pork over mixure. Cover; cook on low heat setting 7-8 hours or until pork and rice are tender.

title: skillet pork and tortilla casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Heat oil in large ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Cook pork and onion 3-4 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in garlic; cook 30 seconds. Stir in corn and flour until well blended. Add salsa, beans and chiles. Bring to boil; simmer, uncovered, 2-3 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Pour into a large bowl. Spoon 1/2 cup pork mixture back into skillet to cover bottom. Arrange half of the tortilla quarters over pork mixture; overlapping slightly. Spoon half of the remaining pork mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle with half the cilantro. Repeat tortilla and pork layers. Bake 25-30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle cheese over pork mixture as soon as it is removed from oven. Top with sour cream and remaining cilantro. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: apple curry soup
directions: Sweat leeks and mushrooms in vegetable oil until tender (without color) in a heavy gauge sauce pot
Add apples, apple cider, coconut milk, curry powder, turmeric. Bring to boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the Chavrie(R) and season with salt and pepper
Pour entire contents in a blender and puree or puree with a hand held mixer

title: breaded pork tenderloin sandwich
directions: Remove the white skin and trim the fat from the tenderloin; cut into four pieces of about 4 to 6 ounces each and pound with the smooth side of a meat tenderizer mallet to a depth of about 1/4 to 3/8 inches. They should and will be bigger than standard sandwich bun.

Prepare the marinade with two eggs, a quart of buttermilk, about 1/4 cup flour, a pinch of salt and pepper, fresh finely chopped garlic, and a tablespoon of dry mustard. For extra punch, add Emeril's Original Essence seasoning can be. Marinate overnight.
Remove the tenderloin from the marinade and let the excess drip off. Coat with breadcrumbs and cornmeal (optional), then let breaded tenderloins set for a couple hours of hours in the refrigerator.

Pre-heat a deep fat fryer filled with canola oil or peanut oil to 360 degrees F. You can also pan fry by pouring in about a 1/4 inch of oil. Fry the tenderloin for approximately 3 minutes or slightly more or until golden brown.
Serve on a bun with sliced tomato, onion, lettuce, mustard or mayo.

title: hazelnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. Grease and flour a cake pan.
In a bowl beat the eggs with the sugar and vanilla sugar until you get a frothy mixture.
Add the milk and oil while mixing.
In a different bowl, mix the flour, yeast, and ground hazelnuts. Add to the wet ingredients.
Mix everything to get a smooth batter.
Fill the prepared cake pan with the mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 400 F.
Feel free to dust with powdered sugar once unmolded.

title: cherry almond coconut bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease an 8 x 12 inch brownie pan and line with baking paper, extending the paper 2 inches over long sides.

Beat the butter, sugar and egg yolk in a small bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Stir in the sifted flours. Press the mixture into the pan. Combine the jam and brandy in a bowl and spread over the mixture in the pan.
To make the topping, beat the eggs and sugar together with a fork in medium bowl, then stir in the coconut.
Sprinkle the topping over the jam mixture then sprinkle the topping with nuts and press down gently.
Bake for about 30 mins, then allow to cool in the pan before cutting.

title: greek-style lamb macaroni
directions: Cook pasta according to package instructions. Drain.
Meanwhile, heat a non-stick deep frying pan over moderate heat. Add sausage; cook, stirring, for 5 minutes or until cooked. Transfer to a heatproof plate.

Heat oil in same pan over moderate heat. Add flour; cook and stir for 1 minute or until bubbling. Gradually whisk in milk until smooth. Cook and whisk for 3 minutes or until sauce boils and thickens. Remove sauce from heat. Add feta, spinach, dill, tomato, sausage and pasta to pan; stir to combine. Season to taste. Serve with lemon wedges and topped with extra dill.

title: huevos rancheros
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F.
Heat 1 tbsp of the oil in a skillet on medium heat. Add onion, garlic and pepper and saute 3 mins, until soft. Stir in tomato and cook 3 mins. Add hot sauce. Season to taste.

Spoon mixture into 4 individual shallow ovenproof dishes. Make a well in center of each dish. Break an egg into a cup and carefully pour into well. Repeat with remaining eggs and dishes. Bake 8 mins, until eggs are set.
Meanwhile, heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in skillet on high heat. Fry tortillas 30 seconds each side, until crisp. Sprinkle egg dishes with cilantro. Serve with tortillas.

title: grilled tomato coconut bbq sauce
directions: Mix oil, garlic powder, ginger and red pepper in large bowl. Add tomatoes, onion and jalapeno; toss to coat. Place vegetables on grill rack or in grill basket.
Grill over medium heat 10 minutes or until vegetables are lightly charred and tender-crisp, turning occasionally. Remove from grill; cool slightly.

Place vegetables in medium saucepan. Stir in coconut milk, salt and pepper. Simmer on low heat 15 to 20 minutes or until flavors are blended, stirring occasionally. Spoon mixture into blender container or food processor; cover. Process until smooth. Serve sauce warm or at room temperature.

title: creamy penne with bacon and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan over moderately high heat. Add mushrooms, bacon and garlic; cook and stir for 2 mins or until mushrooms are almost tender.
Add cream to pan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 3-4 mins or until sauce thickens slightly. Season to taste and remove from heat.
Stir in Parmesan and spinach. Add hot pasta; toss until combined. Spoon into shallow serving bowls. Serve pasta sprinkled with chives.

title: sausage-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Place sliced tomatoes in a large baking dish. Add stock and mushroom caps. Set aside. Melt butter in a frying pan, saute onion and diced mushrooms and season to taste. Add sausage meat and brown. Distribute sausage mixture between mushrooms and sprinkle with cheese and herbes de Provence. Bake for about 20 mins. Serve garnished with parsley.

title: lemon-basil baked chicken
directions: Combine the chicken, basil, garlic, lemon juice, black pepper, curry, cinnamon and olive oil in a Tupperware container and refrigerate for 1/2 an hour or longer.
In a baking dish place the marinated chicken and bake for 35-40 minutes.

title: low carb grilled cheese
directions: Melt the butter.
Combine the butter, egg, flax meal, and baking powder. Mix well.
Spread onto a plate.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Slice bread in half.
Add cheese and either eat it like that or make it like an ordinary grilled cheese sandwich.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water until completely cool.

In large bowl, combine Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Low Fat Mayonnaise Dressing with salsa. Add rotini and remaining ingredients; toss well. Season, if desired, with salt and ground black pepper. Chill, if desired.

title: vegetable soup
directions: To start, chop the garlic and fry it with rosemary olive oil, it will give our future the dish an excellent taste and smell. Then small dice up onion, celery and carrots. Will add them to the garlic and continue stir fry at high temperature.

Then cut dice all the other vegetables as cauliflower and broccoli disassemble the flowers. Once all chopped, put everything in our already roasting vegetables, add a bit more olive oil and mix it will continue cooking for another 5 minutes. Next, close our vegetables reduce cover and leave to stew for 5 - 10 minutes. Add Basil and dill. At this stage, our future can vegetable soup salt and pepper.

Put everything in a pot and fill with water so that she would shut the vegetables. Bring to a boil and add beans. Remove the pan from the heat and put our pots a quarter of the vegetables, chop them in a blender to puree. Put the vegetable puree back in the pan and everything hurt. Let to infuse our soup 20 to 30 minutes and serve.
Bon appetit!

title: herb butter sauce
directions: Melt butter , add other ingredients and simmer for 3-5 minutes.
Pour over cooked vegetables.

title: layered caesar, shrimp & pasta salad
directions: MIX dressing, mayo and garlic.
LAYER half the salad greens, macaroni and tomatoes in 3-qt. bowl. Cover with layers of remaining greens, croutons, eggs, shrimp and cheese. Refrigerate dressing mixture and salad 1 hour.
ADD dressing mixture to salad just before serving; mix lightly.

Heat 1 Tbsp. olive oil and 1 tsp. minced garlic in medium skillet on medium heat. Stir in 1 cup French bread cubes; cook 3 to 4 min. or until crisp and golden brown, stirring frequently. Cool completely.

title: deep-fried catfish
directions: Heat oil to 375 degrees in deep fryer. Stir together flour, salt and pepper. Coat fish with the mixture; dip into eggs, then coat with the bread crumbs. Fry each piece for about 4 minutes or until golden brown.
VARIATION: Prepare thin batter by mixing 1 cup all-purpose flour, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 cup milk and beat till smooth.
Coat fish with flour mixture then dip into batter mixture.

title: wisconsin cheese 'n beer soup
directions: Melt Spread in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat and cook flour, stirring constantly, 3 minutes or until bubbling. Stir in Lipton(R) Recipe Secrets(R) Golden Onion Soup Mix thoroughly blended with milk and Worcestershire sauce. Bring just to the boiling point. Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Garnish, if desired, with additional cheese, chopped red pepper and chopped fresh parsley.
tags: recipe secrets golden onion soup mix

title: bbq chicken pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F. Place pepper and onion in a roasting pan. Spray with oil, toss to coat and bake for 12-15 mins, or until tender.

For the crusts, line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper. While vegetables are roasting combine flours in a bowl. Add milk, 1 cup water and oil. Using hands, mix to form a smooth dough. Divide in half and roll out each half into a 10 inch round. Place on prepared baking sheets and bake 5 mins, or until light golden, then remove from oven.
Top crusts with tomato sauce, roasted vegetables, ham and chicken. Drizzle with barbecue sauce and top with olives and cheeses. Bake for 12-15 mins, or until cheese is melted and golden.

title: coq au vin
directions: Heat the oil in a casserole and fry the chicken and bacon until browned. Remove and set aside. Add the onions and garlic to the pan and fry until softened. Add the carrots and fry for 2 minutes.
Pour in the wine and stock and return the chicken and bacon to the pan. Add the thyme, bay leaves and olives and season with salt and black pepper. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add the cream and bring to a boil. Stir in the cornstarch, bring to a boil again and simmer for 2 minutes.

title: chicken, black olive and mozzarella casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease a baking dish. Heat oil in a frying pan, add chicken and saute for 1-2 mins on each side until cooked through. Remove from pan and arrange in prepared baking dish. Mix parsley, olives, and tomatoes then pour over chicken. Add mozzarella and bake for 25-30 mins. Serve.

title: crispy fish pot pies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease 6 - 4.5 oz ramekins. Place on a baking tray.

In a frying pan, heat butter and oil over high heat. Saute leek for 4-5 mins, until tender. Add flour and cook, stirring, for 1 min. Whisk in cream and wine until smooth then cook, stirring, until mixture boils and thickens. Reduce heat and add fish, lemon and saffron. Simmer for 4-5 mins, until seafood is cooked through. Add sweet potato and dill. Distribute between ramekins.
Meanwhile, to make the topping, combine potato chips, cheese and breadcrumbs. Sprinkle over seafood and bake for 15-20 mins, until golden and bubbling.
Serve with mixed greens.

title: fajita seasoning
directions: mix everything together.
Use 3 Tbsp for 1 lb of meat

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, egg yolks and milk in sauce pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Arrange layer of wafers on bottom and sides of 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Add a layer of banana slices and of pudding.
Continue layering wafers, banana and with pudding mix.
Beat egg whites with salt until foamy throughout.
Gradually beat in sugar and continue beating until mixture will form stiff shiny peaks.
Spoo

title: chicken marsala
directions: Combine 4 tablespoons, salt and pepper in shallow dish. Dip chicken in flour mixture until evenly coated.
Melt 2 tablespoons Promise(R) Buttery Spread in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat and cook chicken, turning once, 10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked. Remove to serving platter and keep warm.

Melt remaining 1 tablespoon Spread in same skillet over medium heat and cook onion and mushrooms, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon flour and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Add wine and cook 1 minute, scraping brown bits from bottom of skillet. Add broth and thyme. Bring to a boil over high heat, then continue boiling, stirring frequently, 2 minutes or until sauce is thickened. To serve, pour sauce over chicken.

title: schnitzel with french fries and bell pepper sauce
directions: Heat the vegetable oil to 325°F. Fry the potatoes in batches for 4-5 mins. Remove using a slotted spoon and set aside.

To make the sauce, heat the sunflower oil in a saucepan, add the onions and peppers and saute for 4-5 mins. Stir in the tomato paste and saute for 1 min. Add 1 tbsp flour and mix well. Stir in the stock and bring to a boil. Simmer for 3-4 mins, stirring. Mix in the paprika and sugar and season with salt and pepper.
Season the pork. Dip each steak with flour then dip in the egg, turning to coat. Press into the breadcrumbs. Heat the butter in a wide frying pan, add the schnitzel and fry, turning for 6-7 mins.

Increase the temperature of the frying oil to 375°F. Fry the potatoes in batches for 2-3 mins until crisp and golden. Drain well and sprinkle with salt. Divide the fries and schnitzel between 4 plates and spoon the sauce on top. Serve.

title: cheating on winter pea soup
directions: In a soup pot, saute onions in coconut oil.
When they become translucent at the salt, pepper and herbs de Provence.
Stir in bok choy, whey and peas.
Simmer for 20 minutes and then remove from the heat.
Using an immersion blender, blend the soup until almost smooth.
Serve warm or cold, with a dollop of plain yogurt or sour cream.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400F.
Wash and dry the unpeeled potatoes.
Rub each potato with a little olive oil on a paper towel, and use a fork to poke holes in each one.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until the potatoes are slightly soft to the touch and the skin gets slightly crispy.
Let cool a little.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Spoon out the inside of the potatoes and mash.
Heat the milk. Add it to the mashed potatoes, add a few slices of butter and grated cheese and mix well to a very creamy puree.
Taste and add more milk or butter if necessary.
Add salt and nutmeg.
Fill the potato halves with the stuffing.
Sprinkle a thin layer of cheese on each half and bake to a gratin.

title: potato and crispy tomatoes waffles
directions: Peel the potatoes, onion, and garlic, then grate in a food processor.
In a bowl, mix the grated ingredients with evaporated milk, eggs, oil, flour, cheese, salt, and pepper.
Mix well and and let stand for 30 minutes.
Cook the waffles in an oiled and preheated waffle iron according to the maker's instructions.

title: herb-seasoned vegetable medley
directions: If using fresh asparagus, snap off woody bases; discard bases. Cut spears into bite-size pieces. Cook fresh asparagus, carrot, bell pepper and green onion in saucepan in small amount of boiling water about 5 minutes or just until tender. (If using frozen asparagus, cook vegetables according to asparagus package directions.) Meanwhile, combine butter, mustard and thyme or basil in small bowl. Drain vegetables; toss with butter mixture.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Mix above ingredients well in a large bowl.
Take a 1/4 cup of the potato mixture and make a pancake in between two sheets of wax paper. Set aside. Continue making cakes with the rest of the mixture.
Add cooking oil to a large saute pan. Once pan is hot add pancakes, two at a time.
Turn to brown on both sides.

title: eggplant "lasagna" bolognese
directions: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan. Cook celery, onion and garlic, stirring, until onion softens. Add ground beef and cook, stirring, until browned. Add tomato sauce and tomato paste. Bring to a boil, stirring, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 mins, or until sauce thickens. Stir in parsley.

Meanwhile, to make the cheese sauce, melt butter in a medium saucepan. Add flour and cook, stirring, until mixture bubbles. Gradually stir in milk then cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens. Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Cook eggplant on a heated, oiled grill pan or frying pan until lightly browned and tender.

Preheat broiler. Divide 1/3 of the bolognese between 6 ovenproof plates. Distribute 1/3 of the spinach and 1 slice of eggplant over top. Spoon 1/3 of the cheese sauce over top. Repeat to make 3 layers. Sprinkle with cheese and broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned. Serve.

title: thai roasted chicken and potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Heat 2 tbsp of the oil in a medium skillet on medium-high heat. Cook shallots for 5-8 mins, until golden. Place in a roasting pan with chicken, potatoes, lemongrass and ginger. Add remaining 4 tbsp oil and lime; toss.
Roast for 40-45 mins, turning chicken and potatoes after 20 mins, until chicken is cooked through. Season.

title: german butchy brioche
directions: Dilute yeast in the lukewarm milk. Cut the butter into small pieces.
Place the flour, salt, sugar, and the eggs in the food processor, then add the milk-yeast mixture.
Knead slowly, and then add the softened butter and knead faster until the dough reaches a smooth and elastic texture.
Transfer to a bowl and let stand covered with a clean dry cloth, in a in a draft-free area for 1-2 hours.

When the dough has doubled in volume, knead well and split into small dough balls of about 50gr. each. Lightly roll out each dough ball and fill them with the sweet potato and chocolate mixture. To close, press both sides and once again form a ball. Place the dough balls in a mold lined with greaseproof paper, spacing them and cover with a cloth. Let stand for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius at least 10 minutes before baking.
Brush the brioche with melted butter and bake for about 20 minutes (more or less depending on the oven) until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack and sprinkle with powdered sugar. The brioche tastes better warm, so it can also be warmed up in a microwave before serving.

title: steak tacos
directions: For black beans, heat 6 tbsp oil in a saucepan and saute onions, thyme and 1/2 the garlic for 2 mins. Add beans and 2/3 cup water, bring to a boil, cover and cook for 1 hour 30 mins, until beans are cooked. Remove from heat, add crushed bouillon cube and season. Transfer to a blender and puree. Allow to cool, stirring occasionally.
For guacamole, combine avocados, lime juice and remaining garlic and puree in a blender. Add yogurt, a pinch of cayenne and season. Add sour cream and mix until smooth.
Heat 2-3 tbsp oil in a frying pan and sear steaks over high heat for 2 mins per side. Season, wrap in foil and let rest for 10 mins. Slice.
Warm tortillas and taco shells according to package instructions. Fill with black beans, guacamole, steak, chili, tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and cilantro.

title: asian smoked chicken
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in the listed ingredients.
To bake, place chicken in cooking bag with some of the marinade.
Puncture bag and bake at 350 degrees until leg moves freely when tested.

title: chop suey hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, celery, & onion.
Add soups, soy sauce, water, salt, & uncooked rice.
Bake 35 to 45 min. in a dish at 350 degrees.
Sprinkle 1 can of Chinese noodles on top & then return to oven.
Bake another 5min. to crisp.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cook the rice according to the package directions.

Heat the oil in a large skillet or wok on medium-high heat. Add the beef and stir fry for 2 mins. Remove from the skillet. Add the onion, garlic, beans, carrots and bamboo shoots and stir fry for 4 mins.

Mix the soy sauce, ketchup, cornstarch, sambal oelek and 1/2 cup water. Add to the skillet and cook for 1 min or until thickened. Add the beef and cashews and stir fry until heated through. Serve over the rice. Garnish with cilantro.

title: vegetable stir fry
directions: Cook the noodles in boiling, salted water for 3-4 mins then drain. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a wok or large frying pan, add the almonds and fry over a medium heat for 2-3 mins until golden. Remove from the pan.

Add 2 tbsp of oil to the frying pan and turn the heat to high. Put the bok choy, scallions, zucchini, ginger and chives into the wok and stir-fry for 4-5 mins. Fold the almonds and noodles into the pan and continue to cook for a further 2-3 mins.
Mix the soy sauce, lime juice and chili sauce together then mix into the pan. Divide between 4 bowls and sprinkle with feta. Serve.

title: goat cheese & dried figs appetizer spoons
directions: Scrape cheese and dice it.
Rinse and chop small chives.
In a bowl blend cheese, small chives, walnut oil, salt and pepper. Cover and set aside for at least 30 mn.
Cut the fig's hard part on top and slice it.
Fill spoons with cheese and top with raisins and dried fig slices.

title: beef - vegetable stir - fry
directions: Peel and thinly slice onions. Arrange on platter with remaining vegetables and beef. (Beef will slice best if partially frozen.) Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, broth and ginger. Set aside.
Heat oil in wok or skillet, over high heat. Add beef and garlic. Stir-fry until lightly browned. Remove from pan. Add vegetables. Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until tender-crisp.

title: golden stuffed pork chops
directions: Using a small knife, make a pocket in chop by cutting into the center from the rib side, parallel to the rib bone and the surface of the chop.
For stuffing, cook onion in butter until transparent and combine with rice, cheese, worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Fill pockets with 3 tablespoons stuffing.

Lightly brown chops in drippings 3-4 minutes per side. Sprinkle with salt, place on rack in roasting pan; cover with foil. Bake at 350 degrees F for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until internal temperature on a thermometer reads 145-160 degrees F. Let rest 3 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni & cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 12-cup muffin pan with cupcake liners; set aside.

Combine 4 tablespoons Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Real Mayonnaise with flour in large microwave-safe bowl with wire whisk. Whisk in 2 tablespoons milk. Microwave at HIGH 1 minute, stirring once. Gradually whisk in remaining milk. Microwave at HIGH 2 minutes, stirring once. Stir in cheese and mustard and let stand 1 minute; stir until smooth. Stir in macaroni, then evenly spoon into prepared muffin pan.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons Mayonnaise with bread crumbs in small bowl. Evenly sprinkle over macaroni. Bake 25 minutes or until crumbs are golden.

title: orange-blueberry smoothie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in blender. Puree until thick and smooth. Pour into glasses. Garnish with blueberries, and a thinly sliced orange peel.

title: italian meatball soup
directions: *** If you can't find Italian diced tomatoes in your store, get regular diced tomatoes and add rosemary, thyme, basil, and oregano.
Bring to a boil, simmer 8-10 minutes or until pasta is tender. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: bistro turkey sandwiches
directions: Combine Hellmann's(R) or Best Foods(R) Light Mayonnaise, tomatoes and basil in large bowl. Spread mayonnaise mixture on bread, then top with turkey and arugula. Slice and serve.

title: bistro smoked turkey sandwiches
directions: Combine Wish-Bone(R) Ranch Dressing, sun-dried tomatoes and basil in small bowl. To assemble sandwiches, spread dressing mixture on rolls, then evenly top with turkey and arugula.

title: apple-apricot crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a large baking dish.
Combine apple and apricots then transfer to prepared dish.

To make the crumble topping, combine graham crackers, butter and sugar in a food processor. Process until mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs. Mix in coconut and oats then sprinkle evenly over fruit. Bake for 25-30 mins, or until golden brown.
Serve with heavy cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: mexican scrambled eggs
directions: Whisk eggs, salt and pepper in large bowl until well blended.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add tortilla strips; cook just until softened, about 15 seconds per batch. Drain on paper towels.

Add green onions and chili to skillet; stir 2 minutes. Reduce heat to medium. Add eggs and tortilla strips to skillet and stir until almost set, about 4 minutes. Add cheese, tomatoes and cilantro. Stir until eggs are set and cheese melts, about 1 minute. Serve immediately.
Adjust spices to your taste. Top with salsa, sour cream or guacamole, or add chorizo.

title: dukkah tandoori chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into nugget sized pieces. Set aside on a plate.
In a a shallow dish, beat the eggs.
In a second plate, put the dukkah tandoori.
Dip pieces of chicken one by one through the eggs and then the dukkah.
Put them in a plate.
Heat some olive oil in a frying pan, add the nuggets, and cook until browned.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put nuts in a preheated dry skillet over medium heat for about 3 - 5 minutes. Watch closely and stir frequently to avoid burning nuts.
Wash and dry basil before using.
Put nuts, olive oil, parmesan cheese, garlic, salt, pepper and lemon juice in a food processor or blender and blend until smooth.
Once mixture is smooth add basil leaves and pulse a few times so the basil doesn't break down too much. If the sauce is too thick add a little more oil
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator. Bring to room temperature before using.

Immediately add the sauce to cooked and drained pasta; the heat from the pasta will warm the sauce. You can also add sauteed chicken or shrimp for the meat eaters. I also like to garnish with fresh diced tomatoes.

title: fish & chips snack mix
directions: In a very large mixing bowl, combine corn chips, fish-shape crackers, oyster crackers, and vegetable sticks.
Store in an airtight container for up to 1 week.
Stir in marshmallows before serving.

title: savory beef muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease and line a 12-cup muffin pan.
To make the filling, heat oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Add ground beef. Brown for 4-5 mins. Add barbecue sauce, tomatoes and feta. Let cool slightly.

Sift flour and baking powder into a large bowl. Add milk, eggs and oil. Whisk until just combined. Half-fill muffin recesses with batter. Distribute filling between recesses then cover with remaining batter. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake for 15-20 mins, until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold with tomato sauce.

title: best chicken parmesan
directions: Depending on how think your chicken breasts are, place them under plastic wrap and pound until thin. If you don't have a meat pounder, use a heavy pot of skillet. You can also fillet these with a knife.
Get 3 pie plates or containers. Put flour in one, beaten eggs in one and bread crumbs in one.
Dredge chicken breast in flour, then in the egg wash, and then the bread crumbs.
Fry cutlets in vegetable oil over med heat. Fry until golden brown.
Spread a little marinara on the bottom of a 13x9 baking dish.

Make a layer of chicken. Add more marinara. Use most of the first quart. Add a layer of the cheeses. Repeat layers. Sprinkle parsley over last layer of cheese. Bake in a pre-heated 350 degree oven covered for 35 minutes. uncover and bake until top is bubbly!

title: ranch deviled eggs
directions: Remove egg yolks, reserving egg whites.

Mash egg yolks in small bowl. Stir in Wish-Bone(R) Ranch Dressing, then season to taste with salt and ground black pepper. Spoon or pipe into egg whites. Chill 1 hour. Garnish, if desired, with parsley and sprinkle with paprika.

title: tofu parsley & raisins salad
directions: Whisk dressing together. In a large bowl, toss herbs with crumbled tofu, raisins and pine nuts. Add dressing and toss to coat.

title: chili con carne burgers
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil in a medium saucepan. Add the rice and return to the boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 20 mins until all the water is absorbed. Melt the butter in another saucepan, add the rice and parsley and cook, stirring often, for a few mins. Remove from the heat; cover to keep warm.
Knead together the ground beef, bread, corn, peppers, onion, jalapeno, egg and mustard. Season with salt and pepper, then shape the mixture into eight small patties.
Heat the chili oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the burgers and cook for 4-5 mins per side until cooked through. Serve the burgers on a bed of parsley rice.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Saute onion and garlic for 2-3 mins, until tender. Add tomato paste and spices. Cook for 1 min. Add ground beef. Cook for 4-5 mins. Add tomatoes and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 mins. Add beans and simmer for 5 mins. Season.
Garnish with fresh cilantro. Serve with rice, tortilla chips, salsa and sour cream.

title: austrian scramble
directions: Directions: Fry bacon until crispy in a large non-stick frying pan.
Set bacon aside to drain.
Add onions to bacon grease except one tablespoon.
Add diced potatoes; mix with the onions.
Add chives, parsley, garlic and salt and pepper, stirring well between each addition.
When thoroughly mixed, pour potatoes in a bowl lined with a paper towel.
Scramble eggs in same pan.
When eggs are almost set, add potato mixture and crumbled bacon; mix thoroughly.
All seasonings are optional.
Experiment with the recipe to find the combination for you.
Eggs may be served separately with the potato-bacon mixture.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and cocoa - mix and add the sour milk which the 2 teaspoons of soda have been added to - mix until blended.
Then slow, add the boiling water, the batter will be very thin.
Bake in a 9 x 13 inch or two 9 inch round pans for 30 minutes at 375 degrees.
Freezes well and stays moist for days.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Heat 1 tbsp of oil in a Dutch oven on medium-high heat. Cook beef in batches for 2-3 mins, until well browned. Remove from pan.
Heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in pan on high heat. Cook shallots and bacon, stirring, for 5 mins, until browned.
Add flour and cook, stirring, for 1 min. Stir in stock and wine. Return beef to pan with mushrooms and bay leaf.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Simmer for 1 hour. Uncover and simmer for another 30 mins, until meat is tender. Sprinkle with parsley and serve with crusty bread.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Grease bottom only of 13 x 9 inch pan.

In large mixer bowl, combine dry cake mix, water and 3 eggs. Blend and beat as directed on package. Pour into prepared pan. In small bowl, beat pumpkin and 2 eggs. Pour evenly over batter. Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sauteed chicken in vodka sauce
directions: Season chicken, if desired, with salt and ground black pepper. Heat Olive Oil in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat and brown chicken. Remove chicken and set aside.

Cook onion and garlic in same skillet, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in vodka and cook 1 minute. Stir in Sauce. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low, then return chicken to skillet. Simmer covered 3 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked. Remove chicken to serving platter and keep warm. Stir in cream and simmer 1 minute or until heated through. Serve, if desired, with hot cooked pasta and garnish with basil.

title: steak salad
directions: Combine 1 tbsp oil, 1 tbsp lime juice and garlic. Rub over steaks. Set aside to marinate.
Meanwhile, combine beans, corn, pepper, radish and cilantro. Combine remaining oil and juice and toss with salad mixture. Season to taste. Set aside.
Heat a grill pan over high heat. Sear steaks for 1 min per side. Season to taste. Let rest for 2 mins then slice and arrange over salad. Serve with tortillas.

title: honey garlic chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients in sauce pan. Heat to boiling and simmer for 5 minutes.
Place 3 lbs chicken wings separated into a 9x13 baking dish. Pour sauce over wings. Marinate for 2 hrs.
Bake at 400 F for 1 hour, turning once.

title: shrimp & grits
directions: Set the Smart Oven+ Attachment base pan with heating element and Steamer Water Basin Pan on the oven rack. Fill Water Basin Pan with 4 cups of water.

Place grits in 9" x 13" casserole dish. Place casserole dish on Perforated Steamer Tray and set in Water Basin Pan. Pour 31/2 cups boiling water over the top of grits. Place Lid on Steamer. On STEAM mode, steam grits for 45-60 minutes, until they begin to thicken. Stir in 2 tablespoons butter, jalapeno, cream and tabasco. Season with salt and pepper. Turn oven off but leave Lid on Steamer to keep grits warm while preparing the shrimp.

Cook bacon in large skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic, shallot and remaining butter to skillet. When butter has melted, add shrimp to skillet. Deglaze pan with wine and chicken stock; cook until shrimp is cooked through, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat and squeeze lemon over top.
To serve, divide grits between bowls. Spoon shrimp into center of bowls and serve immediately with chopped parsley.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Sift flour into a large bowl. Stir in chocolate chips, sugar and a pinch of salt.
Whisk milk, egg and butter in a medium bowl until combined. Add to dry ingredients, whisking until smooth.
Heat a large nonstick skillet on medium heat. Brush with a little melted butter.
Drop level tablespoonfuls of the batter into pan and cook for 1-2 mins, until bubbles appear on the surface. Turn and cook the other side for 1 min or until golden.
Repeat with remaining batter, brushing the pan between batches. Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: fancy seafood
directions: Combine vegetable, crab meat or shrimp, red pepper, and mayonnaise; place mixture in 1 quart casserole.
Toss crumbs in butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until hot and crumbs are golden brown.
Yields 6-8.

title: hot & spicy ribs
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over low heat. Add onion and garlic. Saute until tender. Add remaining ingredients except ribs and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Place large piece of aluminum foil over coals beneath grill to catch drippings. Baste meatiest side of ribs with sauce. Place ribs on grill meatiest side down 6 inches above low coals. Baste top side, close hood, cook 20 minutes, turn and baste. Cook additional 45 minutes or until done. Basting every 10-15 minutes with sauce.

title: blue cheese stuffed prunes
directions: Prepare the walnuts first, by heating a small saute pan on medium heat. Add the walnuts and continually toss until the walnuts become fragrant. Remove from heat. Put on a cutting board and use rolling pin or (carefully) pint glass over the walnuts to crush them.
In a small bowl, crumble the blue cheese and mash with a fork. Add the walnuts, white wine and half and half. Stir into a paste.

Make sure none of the prunes have pits, if so, remove them. Take a small object like a chopstick to open them. Carefully spoon the blue cheese mixture into the hole. I used the opposite end of a small spoon, because the opening is pretty small. Wipe off any excess blue cheese from the sides. Place on plate. Garnish with fresh or dried parsley. Serve immediately, or refrigerate for a few hours before serving. Can be eaten as a small bite for a cocktail or wine with friends.

title: pork pot stickers and green curry-coconut sauce
directions: For pot sticker filling: Combine all ingredients (pork tenderloin, soy sauce, grated ginger, lemon grass, fresh basil, 1/2 tsp kosher salt, garlic, white pepper) in a food processor; puree until smooth. Brush wonton wrappers lightly with water on one side. Place about 2 teaspoons of filling in the center of each wrapper. Fold the wrapper up around the filling, pressing to seal in pork filling. Set aside.

For sauce: In a large saucepan, stir together all ingredients (coconut milk, chicken broth, lime juice and zest, curry paste, 1/4 tsp kosher salt); bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat. Set aside.

In a large skillet, heat 2 Tbs oil over medium heat until hot. Place pot stickers in the skillet; brown both sides. When pot stickers are brown, pour sauce in skillet. Bring to a boil; simmer for 1 minute. Serve pot stickers on plate, spoon sauce over top.
Serve with Green Papaya Cole Slaw: https://www.yummly.com/recipe/Green-Papaya-Cole-Slaw-2248263

title: green papaya cole slaw
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients (papaya, bok choy, carrots, red bell pepper, red onion, fresh cilantro, fresh mint) except dressing; set aside. In small bowl, combine dressing ingredients (rice vinegar, honey, grape seed oil, ginger root); pour over vegetable mixture. Stir to combine; set aside for at least 15 minutes to allow flavors to develop.
Garnish with chives or red bell pepper strips.

Serve with Pork Pot Stickers and Green Curry-Coconut Sauce.
Link for Pot Stickers: https://www.yummly.com/recipe/Pork-Pot-Stickers-and-Green-Curry-Coconut-Sauce-2249148

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400degrees and fill muffin tin with paper cups.

Measure the dry ingredients into a large bowl. Pour all the liquid ingredients into a measuring cup. Mix both together, remembering that a lumpy batter makes teh best muffins. Spoon into waiting cups. Sprinkle more chocolate chips on top, then cook for 20 minutes until muffins are dark, risen and springy.

title: stuffed filet mignon
directions: Slice meat 3/4 of the way down.
Top with strips of bacon.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: gluten-free vanilla waffles with orange curd
directions: In a heavy bottomed saucepan, whisk together the butter and egg yolks. Once mixed through, whisk in the honey, orange juice, and lemon juice and cook over medium heat, continually whisking through, until it thickens and can coat the back of a spoon.
Once thickened, remove from the heat and mix in the orange zest.
Pour the orange curd into a glass container, and cover the top with a dampened cloth or paper towel to avoid a crust from forming.
Place in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight to chill and thicken.
For the gluten-free vanilla waffles

In a large bowl whisk together the oat flour, baking powder, and salt. Add in the eggs, honey, vanilla extract, and milk; whisk together into a batter. *the batter may seem runny, allow it to sit for 5 minutes or so to thicken.
Cook the waffles in your KitchenAid(R) Waffle Baker according to the manufacturer's directions.
Serve the waffles topped with orange curd. To make it extra special, warm the curd and sprinkle with ground cinnamon.

title: tarragon chicken with crisp potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F.
Combine oil, lemon peel and juice, and tarragon in a large baking dish. Add drumsticks, season to taste and toss to coat. Bake for 1 hour or until cooked through.

Place potatoes in a microwave-safe dish. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on high (100%) for 5 mins, until partially cooked. Arrange in a single layer on a baking pan. Season to taste. Bake in oven with chicken for 40-45 mins, until golden.
Serve chicken with crisp potatoes and arugula salad.

title: baked zucchini chips
directions: Preheat oven to 375F
Slice zucchini into thin and even slices
Brush each "chip" with olive oil and then place on a baking sheet
Add cayenne pepper, salt and pepper
Bake for 30-45 minutes or until crisp
